und. SOL amounts. Oracle info replaces commit-reveal fairness section.\n   282→\n   283→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors, 128 pre-existing warnings) + `pnpm typecheck` (0 errors)\n   284→\n   285→## Iteration 30 — 2026-03-17T20:08:18Z — OK\n   286→- **Log**: iteration-030.log\n   287→\n   288→## Iteration 31 — 2026-03-17T20:09:20Z — OK\n   289→- **Log**: iteration-031.log\n   290→\n   291→## Iteration 32 — 2026-03-17T20:10:07Z — OK\n   292→- **Log**: iteration-032.log\n   293→\n   294→## Iteration 33 — 2026-03-17T20:10:54Z — OK\n   295→- **Log**: iteration-033.log\n   296→\n   297→## Iteration 34 — 2026-03-17T20:11:44Z — OK\n   298→- **Log**: iteration-034.log\n   299→\n   300→## Iteration 35 — 2026-03-17T20:12:50Z — OK\n   301→- **Log**: iteration-035.log\n   302→\n   303→## Iteration 36 — 2026-03-17T20:13:55Z — OK\n   304→- **Log**: iteration-036.log\n   305→\n   306→## Iteration 37 — 2026-03-17T20:17:49Z — OK\n   307→- **Log**: iteration-037.log\n   308→\n   309→## Iteration 39 — Rewrite CloseCallContext with real backend + Pyth price\n   310→\n   311→**Item**: [frontend] Rewrite CloseCallContext.tsx — replace mock-simulation with backend API + price-feeds\n   312→\n   313→**Result**: PASS\n   314→\n   315→**Changes**:\n   316→- `apps/platform/package.json`: Added `@rng-utopia/price-feeds` workspace dependency\n   317→- `apps/platform/src/App.tsx`: Added `PriceFeedProvider` wrapper from `@rng-utopia/price-feeds` at app root level (enables `usePriceSubscription` for all features)\n   318→- `apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`: Full rewrite:\n   319→  - Removed all `mock-simulation.ts` imports (initializeGame, subscribeToRound, subscribeToCompletedRound, getCurrentRound, getUserHistory, getRecentCandles, getCurrentCandle, getCandleProgress, isGameInitialized, clearCompletedRound)\n   320→  - Added `usePriceSubscription(\"BTC\")` from `@rng-utopia/price-feeds` for live BTC/USD price\n   321→  - Added backend API integration: `fetchCurrentRound()` (GET /closecall/current-round), `fetchRoundHistory()` (GET /closecall/history)\n   322→  - Backend URL follows coinflip/lord pattern: `VITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL` env var\n   323→  - `backendToRound()` converter: maps backend JSON → frontend `Round` type (lamports→SOL conversion, entry arrays→PlayerBet arrays)\n   324→  - 2-second polling interval for current round data\n   325→  - Round transition detection via `prevRoundIdRef` — auto-fetches completed round for result overlay\n   326→  - Local candle builder from Pyth price ticks (accumulates 1-min OHLC, keeps 15 completed + current forming candle)\n   327→  - `candleProgress` computed from real clock time (ms into current minute / 60000)\n   328→  - User history loaded from backend settled rounds, filtered by wallet address\n   329→  - `placeBet()` kept as validation-only stub with TODO for next iteration (wallet tx)\n   330→\n   331→**Notes**:\n   332→- `mock-simulation.ts` and `candle-replay.ts` are no longer imported by the context but NOT deleted yet (spec says \"Remove mock-simulation.ts if fully replaced\" is deferred to the place_bet wiring iteration)\n   333→- `payout-calculator.ts` still used for `calculatePotentialPayout` and user history payout estimation\n   334→- PriceFeedProvider placed at app root (not inside CloseCallProvider) to avoid WebSocket reconnection on navigation and to support future features needing Pyth data\n   335→\n   336→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors, 128 pre-existing warnings) + `pnpm typecheck` (0 errors) + `pnpm build` (success)\n   337→\n   338→## Iteration 39 — 2026-03-18T04:53:15Z — OK\n   339→- **Log**: iteration-039.log\n   340→\n   341→## Iteration 40 — Wire wallet integration for place_bet\n   342→\n   343→**Item**: [frontend] Wire wallet integration for `place_bet` in CloseCallContext.tsx\n   344→\n   345→**Result**: PASS\n   346→\n   347→**Changes**:\n   348→- `apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`:\n   349→  - Added imports: `useConnection`, `useBalance` from wallet hooks; `Program`, `AnchorProvider`, `BN` from `@coral-xyz/anchor`; `PublicKey`, `SystemProgram`, `Transaction` from `@solana/web3.js`; `ClosecallIDL` + `Closecall` type from anchor-client\n   350→  - Added local PDA helpers: `getCloseCallConfigPda()`, `getCloseCallRoundPda()` (defined locally to avoid Buffer polyfill issues from game-engine import in browser build)\n   351→  - Added `getClosecallProgram(connection)` — read-only Anchor program instance\n   352→  - Added `buildPlaceBetTx(connection, player, roundId, side, amountSol)` — builds `place_bet` instruction via Anchor, sets feePayer + blockhash\n   353→  - Added `parseTransactionError(err)` — maps Solana/Anchor errors to user-friendly messages (insufficient balance, betting closed, already bet, max entries, paused, user rejected, network error, simulation failure, blockhash expiry)\n   354→  - Added `sendAndConfirm(transaction)` in provider — pre-flight simulation, 3 retry attempts on blockhash expiry, fallback signature status check, balance refresh on success (exact coinflip pattern)\n   355→  - Replaced `placeBet()` stub with real implementation: validates wallet connection, bet side, amount, balance, round phase, betting window; builds + sends on-chain tx; clears pending side on success; refreshes round on betting-closed race condition\n   356→  - Moved `refreshRound` and `clearCompletedRound` before `sendAndConfirm`/`placeBet` to avoid temporal dead zone\n   357→  - Destructured `publicKey`, `sendTransaction` from `useWallet()`; `connection` from `useConnection()`; `refreshBalance` from `useBalance()`\n   358→- Deleted `utils/mock-simulation.ts` — no longer imported by anything (context uses real backend API)\n   359→- Deleted `utils/candle-replay.ts` — only imported by mock-simulation.ts\n   360→- Kept `utils/payout-calculator.ts` — still used by context for `calculatePotentialPayout`\n   361→\n   362→**Notes**:\n   363→- Could not import PDA helpers from `@rng-utopia/game-engine` because that module uses `Buffer.from()` which triggers a missing polyfill error in Vite's browser build (`Rollup failed to resolve import \"vite-plugin-node-polyfills/shims/buffer\"`). Defined helpers locally, matching the coinflip pattern in `chain.ts`.\n   364→- `payout-calculator.ts` NOT deleted (still used for potential payout display). Spec says \"Remove if fully replaced\" — it's not fully replaced.\n   365→\n   366→**Verification**: `pnpm lint` (0 errors, 130 pre-existing warnings) + `pnpm typecheck` (0 errors) + `pnpm build` (success)\n   367→\n   368→## Iteration 40 — 2026-03-18T05:03:28Z — OK\n   369→- **Log**: iteration-040.log\n   370→\n   371→## Iteration 41 — Close Call deep-link round page\n   372→\n   373→**Item**: [frontend] Add `/close-call/:roundId` deep-link page\n   374→\n   375→**Result**: PASS\n   376→\n   377→**Changes**:\n   378→- `apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallRoundPage.tsx`: New page component fetching from `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/:roundId`. Displays: oracle prices (open/close from Pyth BTC/USD), outcome (Green/Red/Refund with color), pool breakdown (green/red pool amounts + entry counts), total pool, fee collected, entries list (player addresses + amounts per side), settlement tx (links to Solana Explorer), settled timestamp, verification info (price source + resolution logic). Loading/error states with back-link to `/close-call`. Row component supports ReactNode labels, copy-to-clipboard with optional copyValue override.\n   379→- `apps/platform/src/App.tsx`: Added import for `CloseCallRoundPage`, added route `<Route path=\"/close-call/:roundId\" element={<CloseCallRoundPage />} />`.\n   380→- `apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallPage.tsx`: Added `Link` import from react-router-dom. Changed history modal \"Verify on Fairness Page\" link to `Link` pointing to `/close-call/${round.id}` (\"View Round Details\").\n   381→\n   382→**Notes**:\n   383→- Follows LordRoundPage pattern but adapted for oracle