{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01WBhmiLJBZjiUdNQ24R8Tx5","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile all the information into a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Summary: Close Call Backend API & Clock Worker\n\n### **API Endpoints** (`closecall.ts`)\n\n#### **1. GET `/closecall/current-round`**\n- **Purpose**: Get the active (open) round + pool state\n- **Response**: \n```json\n{\n  \"round\": {\n    \"roundId\": \"string (8-byte hex)\",\n    \"pda\": \"string (base58)\",\n    \"phase\": \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\",\n    \"openPrice\": number,\n    \"openPriceExpo\": number,\n    \"closePrice\": number | null,\n    \"outcome\": \"pending\" | \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\",\n    \"greenPool\": number (lamports),\n    \"redPool\": number (lamports),\n    \"totalPool\": number,\n    \"totalFee\": number,\n    \"greenEntries\": [{ player: string, amountLamports: number }, ...],\n    \"redEntries\": [{ player: string, amountLamports: number }, ...],\n    \"greenCount\": number,\n    \"redCount\": number,\n    \"settleTx\": string | null,\n    \"createdAt\": ISO8601,\n    \"settledAt\": ISO8601 | null\n  }\n}\n```\n- If no active round: `{ \"round\": null }`\n\n#### **2. GET `/closecall/history?limit=20`**\n- **Purpose**: Get the last N settled/refunded rounds\n- **Query params**: `limit` (default 20, max 100)\n- **Response**: \n```json\n{\n  \"rounds\": [{ same shape as above }, ...]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Clock Worker** (`closecall-clock.ts`)\n\nThe worker creates and settles Close Call rounds on minute boundaries.\n\n#### **Tick Cycle** (aligned to ~2 seconds after each minute):\n1. **Settle previous round** (if exists and candle closed)\n2. **Create new round** (reads Pyth open price on-chain)\n\n#### **Settlement Logic**:\n- Reads current Pyth BTC/USD price + treasury address\n- Determines outcome:\n  - **Refund**: If no players, one-sided betting, single player, or price unchanged\n  - **Green wins**: `closePrice > openPrice`\n  - **Red wins**: `closePrice < openPrice`\n- Builds settlement tx with filtered remaining accounts:\n  - Refund: all players (green then red)\n  - Green/Red: only winning side players\n- Submits tx with retry logic (max 3 attempts, 2s delay)\n\n#### **Round Creation**:\n- Generates random 8-byte `roundId`\n- Reads Pyth price account for open price\n- Stores on-chain via CloseCallCreateRound instruction\n- Logs roundId (hex), PDA, tx sig\n\n#### **Recovery**:\n- On start: scans for existing OPEN phase rounds owned by server\n- Restarts settlement/creation cycle cleanly\n\n#### **Key Constants**:\n- Tick offset: 2 seconds after minute boundary\n- Max retries: 3 per tx\n- Retry delay: 2 seconds\n- Pyth price offsets: offset 73 for price (i64), offset 89 for exponent (i32)\n\n---\n\n### **Rounds/Fairness Route** (`rounds.ts`)\n\n#### **GET `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId`**\n- Takes 16-char hex matchId\n- Checks `rounds` table first (commit-reveal games)\n- Falls back to `closecall_rounds` table\n- Returns formatted response (settled rounds expose secret + verification payload)\n\n#### **GET `/fairness/rounds/:pda`**\n- Get by round PDA (primary key)\n- Returns same formatted response\n\n#### **Close Call Response Shape** (when isSettled):\n```json\n{\n  \"pda\": string,\n  \"game\": \"closecall\",\n  \"phase\": \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\",\n  \"matchId\": string (roundId),\n  \"openPrice\": number,\n  \"openPriceExpo\": number,\n  \"greenPool\": number,\n  \"redPool\": number,\n  \"totalPool\": number,\n  \"greenEntries\": [...],\n  \"redEntries\": [...],\n  \"greenCount\": number,\n  \"redCount\": number,\n  \"createdAt\": ISO8601,\n  \"closePrice\": number (when settled),\n  \"outcome\": \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\" (when settled),\n  \"totalFee\": number (when settled),\n  \"settleTx\": string (when settled),\n  \"settledAt\": ISO8601 (when settled),\n  \"verification\": {\n    \"priceSource\": \"Pyth Network push oracle\",\n    \"outcome\": \"close > open\" | \"close < open\" | \"refund (...)\"\n  }\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Database Schema** (`db.ts`)\n\n**CloseCallRound interface**:\n- `round_id`: string (8-byte hex)\n- `pda`: string (base58)\n- `server_key`: string\n- `phase`: \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\"\n- `open_price`: number\n- `open_price_expo`: number\n- `close_price`: number | null\n- `outcome`: \"pending\" | \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\"\n- `green_pool`, `red_pool`: number (lamports)\n- `total_fee`: number\n- `green_entries`, `red_entries`: Array<{ player: string, amountLamports: number }>\n- `settle_tx`: string | null\n- `created_at`, `settled_at`: Date\n\n**Key DB Methods**:\n- `insertCloseCallRound(roundId, pda, serverKey, openPrice, openPriceExpo)`\n- `getCloseCallCurrentRound()` — OPEN phase only\n- `getCloseCallHistory(limit)` — settled/refunded\n- `getCloseCallRound(roundId)` — by hex ID\n- `settleCloseCallRound(roundId, updates)` — update after settlement\n\n---\n\n**File Paths**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/closecall.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts`\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/db.ts`"},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: aa223947d6577a2d6 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 44940\ntool_uses: 10\nduration_ms: 45538</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1de1cbce-bcf6-4659-9a0e-c65f55d25303","uuid":"4e75cdbb-53ba-4fa1-9bb7-27b5795747be","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read the following files to understand the Close Call backend API and clock worker:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/closecall.ts` - API routes\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/worker/closecall-clock.ts` - Clock worker\n3. `sources/rng-utopia/services/backend/src/routes/rounds.ts` - Rounds/fairness routes (for the closecall extension)\n\nI need to understand:\n- What API endpoints exist for close call\n- Request/response shapes\n- How rounds are created and settled\n- What the current round response looks like","agentId":"aa223947d6577a2d6","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile all the information into a comprehensive summary:\n\n## Summary: Close Call Backend API & Clock Worker\n\n### **API Endpoints** (`closecall.ts`)\n\n#### **1. GET `/closecall/current-round`**\n- **Purpose**: Get the active (open) round + pool state\n- **Response**: \n```json\n{\n  \"round\": {\n    \"roundId\": \"string (8-byte hex)\",\n    \"pda\": \"string (base58)\",\n    \"phase\": \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\",\n    \"openPrice\": number,\n    \"openPriceExpo\": number,\n    \"closePrice\": number | null,\n    \"outcome\": \"pending\" | \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\",\n    \"greenPool\": number (lamports),\n    \"redPool\": number (lamports),\n    \"totalPool\": number,\n    \"totalFee\": number,\n    \"greenEntries\": [{ player: string, amountLamports: number }, ...],\n    \"redEntries\": [{ player: string, amountLamports: number }, ...],\n    \"greenCount\": number,\n    \"redCount\": number,\n    \"settleTx\": string | null,\n    \"createdAt\": ISO8601,\n    \"settledAt\": ISO8601 | null\n  }\n}\n```\n- If no active round: `{ \"round\": null }`\n\n#### **2. GET `/closecall/history?limit=20`**\n- **Purpose**: Get the last N settled/refunded rounds\n- **Query params**: `limit` (default 20, max 100)\n- **Response**: \n```json\n{\n  \"rounds\": [{ same shape as above }, ...]\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Clock Worker** (`closecall-clock.ts`)\n\nThe worker creates and settles Close Call rounds on minute boundaries.\n\n#### **Tick Cycle** (aligned to ~2 seconds after each minute):\n1. **Settle previous round** (if exists and candle closed)\n2. **Create new round** (reads Pyth open price on-chain)\n\n#### **Settlement Logic**:\n- Reads current Pyth BTC/USD price + treasury address\n- Determines outcome:\n  - **Refund**: If no players, one-sided betting, single player, or price unchanged\n  - **Green wins**: `closePrice > openPrice`\n  - **Red wins**: `closePrice < openPrice`\n- Builds settlement tx with filtered remaining accounts:\n  - Refund: all players (green then red)\n  - Green/Red: only winning side players\n- Submits tx with retry logic (max 3 attempts, 2s delay)\n\n#### **Round Creation**:\n- Generates random 8-byte `roundId`\n- Reads Pyth price account for open price\n- Stores on-chain via CloseCallCreateRound instruction\n- Logs roundId (hex), PDA, tx sig\n\n#### **Recovery**:\n- On start: scans for existing OPEN phase rounds owned by server\n- Restarts settlement/creation cycle cleanly\n\n#### **Key Constants**:\n- Tick offset: 2 seconds after minute boundary\n- Max retries: 3 per tx\n- Retry delay: 2 seconds\n- Pyth price offsets: offset 73 for price (i64), offset 89 for exponent (i32)\n\n---\n\n### **Rounds/Fairness Route** (`rounds.ts`)\n\n#### **GET `/fairness/rounds/by-id/:matchId`**\n- Takes 16-char hex matchId\n- Checks `rounds` table first (commit-reveal games)\n- Falls back to `closecall_rounds` table\n- Returns formatted response (settled rounds expose secret + verification payload)\n\n#### **GET `/fairness/rounds/:pda`**\n- Get by round PDA (primary key)\n- Returns same formatted response\n\n#### **Close Call Response Shape** (when isSettled):\n```json\n{\n  \"pda\": string,\n  \"game\": \"closecall\",\n  \"phase\": \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\",\n  \"matchId\": string (roundId),\n  \"openPrice\": number,\n  \"openPriceExpo\": number,\n  \"greenPool\": number,\n  \"redPool\": number,\n  \"totalPool\": number,\n  \"greenEntries\": [...],\n  \"redEntries\": [...],\n  \"greenCount\": number,\n  \"redCount\": number,\n  \"createdAt\": ISO8601,\n  \"closePrice\": number (when settled),\n  \"outcome\": \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\" (when settled),\