{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Htx8ZWX4vyLDd2cFD99RLr","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of the Close Call frontend structure with DOM selectors for E2E testing. Here's my analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Close Call Frontend: Complete DOM & State Reference\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\n**Key Context Providers:**\n- `CloseCallContext` (from `/CloseCallContext.tsx`) — manages round state, betting, price subscription, and on-chain interaction\n- `CloseCallProvider` wraps the content and provides context via `useCloseCall()` hook\n\n**Page Structure:**\n- **`CloseCallPage.tsx`** — Main game page (renders `CloseCallPageContent` inside provider)\n- **`CloseCallRoundPage.tsx`** — Deep-link detail page for completed rounds (fetches from `/fairness/rounds/by-id/{roundId}`)\n\n---\n\n### Round State Visualization\n\n#### How Frontend Displays Round State\n\n| Round Phase | UI Indicators | Context State |\n|-------------|---------------|---------------|\n| **Initial Load** | Spinner + \"Loading chart...\" | `loading: true`, `currentRound: null` |\n| **Open (Betting)** | Chart visible, Bet buttons enabled, Progress bar white (0-10s) | `currentRound.phase: \"open\"`, `Date.now() < currentRound.bettingEndsAt` |\n| **Locked (No Betting)** | Chart visible, Bet buttons disabled, Progress bar gray (10-60s) | `currentRound.phase: \"open\"`, `Date.now() >= currentRound.bettingEndsAt` |\n| **Settled/Refunded** | Result banner visible, new round starts polling | `currentRound: null`, `completedRound: { outcome: \"green\" \\| \"red\" \\| \"refund\" }` |\n| **Backend Unavailable** | No round shown, no chart | `fetchCurrentRound()` returns `null`, `loading: true` (after retry) |\n\n---\n\n### Wallet Connection States\n\n#### Connected Wallet\n- **Sidebar buttons render:** `SideSelector` component with GREEN/RED buttons\n- **Bet amount input:** Enabled (unless user already bet or betting closed)\n- **Expected DOM:**\n  - Button with class `close-call-side-btn--green`\n  - Button with class `close-call-side-btn--red`\n  - Input with class `close-call-bet-input__field`\n\n#### Disconnected Wallet\n- **Single button rendered:** `<button className=\"close-call-action-btn\">Connect Wallet</button>`\n- **Clicking triggers:** `connect()` from wallet adapter\n- **Expected DOM:**\n  - Button containing text: \"Connect Wallet\"\n  - Class: `close-call-action-btn`\n\n---\n\n### Backend Availability States\n\n#### Backend Running (Healthy)\n- Polls `/closecall/current-round` every 2s (line 413)\n- If round exists: displays chart, pool, candles\n- If round settled: fetches `/fairness/rounds/by-id/{roundId}` to show completion\n- Expected: Round displays normally within 2s of load\n\n#### Backend Down / Unreachable\n- `fetchCurrentRound()` catches all errors → returns `null` (line 118)\n- Frontend shows: Empty state (no chart, no round data)\n- **Does NOT show error message** — silently falls back to null\n- Retries continue every 2s in background\n- Expected: No crash, just blank sidebar/main area until backend recovers\n\n**Note:** Error handling is silent by design. No error toast or error message shown to player if backend is unavailable initially.\n\n---\n\n### DOM Selectors for E2E Tests\n\n#### Main Page Structure\n```\n[Main Container]\n  .close-call-main                           # Main game area\n    .close-call-main__banner                 # \"Will the current candle close GREEN or RED?\"\n    .close-call-main__loading                # Shows when loading === true\n    .close-call-main__spinner                # Spinner div (child of loading)\n    [CandlestickChart]                       # Chart component (when not loading)\n\n[Sidebar]\n  .close-call-sidebar\n    .close-call-sidebar__section             # Multiple sections: input, buttons, pool, fairness info\n```\n\n#### Chart Component Selectors\n```\n.close-call-chart\n  .close-call-chart__header\n    .close-call-chart__asset-name            # Text: \"BTC/USD 1 min\"\n  .close-call-chart__container\n    .close-call-chart__lw-chart              # Lightweight Charts container (ref)\n    .close-call-chart__price-panel           # Right-side price display\n      .close-call-chart__current-price       # Colored current price (green/red)\n      .close-call-chart__ohl                 # O, H, L price rows\n  .close-call-chart__footer\n    .close-call-chart__progress              # Progress bar container\n      .close-call-chart__progress-fill--betting  # White fill (0-10s)\n      .close-call-chart__progress-fill--locked   # Gray fill (10-60s)\n    .close-call-chart__label\n      .close-call-chart__label--betting      # \"BETTING OPEN • Ns to bet\" (when open)\n      .close-call-chart__label--locked       # \"BETTING LOCKED • Candle Close in Ns\" (when locked)\n```\n\n#### Bet Amount Input Selectors\n```\n.close-call-bet-input\n  .close-call-bet-input__label               # \"Bet Amount ($)\"\n  .close-call-bet-input__field               # Input field (text, decimal mode)\n  .close-call-bet-input__btn                 # Adjustment buttons: ½, 2x, MAX\n  .close-call-bet-input__range               # \"Min: X  Max: Y\"\n\n[Disabled state]\n  .close-call-bet-input--disabled            # Applied to container when disabled\n```\n\n#### Side Selector (Bet Buttons) Selectors\n```\n.close-call-side-selector\n  .close-call-side-btn.close-call-side-btn--green\n    .close-call-side-btn__label              # Text: \"GREEN\" or \"Joining...\"\n  .close-call-side-btn.close-call-side-btn--red\n    .close-call-side-btn__label              # Text: \"RED\" or \"Joining...\"\n\n[Selected state]\n  .close-call-side-btn--selected             # Applied to active button\n\n[Disabled state]\n  .close-call-side-selector--disabled        # Applied to container\n```\n\n#### Pool Distribution Selectors\n```\n.close-call-pool-bar\n  .close-call-pool-bar__labels\n    .close-call-pool-bar__label--green       # Green %\n    .close-call-pool-bar__label--red         # Red %\n  .close-call-pool-bar__track\n    .close-call-pool-bar__fill--green        # Green pool width\n    .close-call-pool-bar__fill--red          # Red pool width\n  .close-call-pool-bar__stats\n    .close-call-pool-bar__pool-amount        # Pool SOL amounts\n    .close-call-pool-bar__odds               # Odds multiplier (~Nx)\n  .close-call-pool-bar__prize\n    .close-call-pool-bar__prize-label        # \"PRIZE POOL\"\n    .close-call-pool-bar__prize-amount\n      .close-call-pool-bar__prize-sol        # Total pool SOL display\n  \n  [User Bet Active]\n  .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet-header    # \"Joined GREEN\" or \"Joined RED\"\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet-row       # Amount row\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet-value     # \"X.XXXX SOL\"\n    \n    [If User Won]\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet--won      # Container modifier\n    .close-call-pool-bar__win-animation      # Star/coin animation\n    .close-call-pool-bar__stars              # Star elements\n    .close-call-pool-bar__coins              # Coin elements\n    \n    [If User Lost]\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet--lost     # Container modifier\n    .close-call-pool-bar__loss-animation     # Heartbreak emoji animation\n```\n\n#### Result Banner Selectors\n```\n.close-call-main > [RoundResultBanner]       # Component from @rng-utopia/ui\n  [Rendered when completedRound !== null]\n  [Shows: \"GREEN WINS\" / \"RED WINS\" / \"REFUND\"]\n  [Shows: \"You Won!\" / \"You Lost\" / \"Bet refunded\" + payout amount]\n```\n\n#### History Modal Selectors\n```\n.close-call-history-modal\n  .close-call-history-modal__section         # Multiple sections: Stats, Candle Data, Oracle Verification\n  .close-call-history-modal__section-title   # Section headers\n  .close-call-history-modal__row              # Label/value pairs\n  .close-call-history-modal__hash            # Monospace hash display (copyable)\n  .close-call-history-modal__verify-link     # \"View Round Details →\" link to /close-call/{roundId}\n\n[History Entry List - from GameLayout]\n  .close-call-history-result                 # History row result display\n  .close-call-history-result__separator      # \"|\" separator\n```\n\n#### Payout Message Selectors (Completed Round)\n```\n.close-call-payout-received                  # Shows under pool when user won\n  .close-call-payout-received__label         # \"Payout Received!\"\n  .close-call-payout-received__amount        # \"+X.XXXX SOL\"\n```\n\n#### Fairness Info Selectors\n```\n.close-call-sidebar__fairness\n  .close-call-sidebar__fairness-title        # \"Round Info\"\n  .close-call-sidebar__fairness-row          # \"Round ID\" and \"Oracle\" rows\n  .close-call-sidebar__hash                  # Hash display (last 12 chars of roundId)\n```\n\n#### Round Details Page (`/close-call/{roundId}`)\n```\n[Main container: max-width 640px, centered]\n  [Back link] → \"/close-call\"\n  <h2>Close Call Round Details</h2>\n  \n  [Status section]\n    \"Round ID\", \"Status\", \"Created\"\n  \n  [Oracle Prices section]\n    \"Open Price\", \"Close Price\" (if settled), \"Outcome\" (if settled)\n  \n  [Pool section]\n    \"Green Pool\", \"Red Pool\", \"Total Pool\", \"Fee Collected\" (if settled)\n  \n  [Entries section]\n    GREEN entries list, RED entries list (with addresses and amounts)\n  \n  [Settlement section] (if settled)\n    \"Settled At\", \"Settlement Tx\", \"Price Source\", \"Resolution\"\n    Verification explanation paragraph (text color: #94a3b8)\n  \n  [Open Round message]\n    \"Round is still open. Outcome and close price will be available after settlement.\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Context Hook Values (Key Selectors)\n\nFrom `useCloseCall()`, you can test:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  // Round data\n  currentRound: {\n    id: string;                    // e.g., \"0x1234...abcd\" (hex)\n    phase: \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\";\n    pool: { greenPool, redPool, totalPool, greenBets[], redBets[] };\n    outcome: \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\" | undefined;\n    bettingEndsAt: timestamp;\n  },\n  completedRound: Round | null,   // Previous round after settlement\n  \n  // Loading\n  loading: boolean;                // true on initial load, false after first poll\n  placingBet: boolean;             // true during tx send/confirm\n  \n  // User interaction\n  currentPrice: number;            // BTC price from Pyth\n  candleProgress: number;          // 0-1, progress through 60s candle\n  userBet: PlayerBet | null;       // User's active bet in current round\n  pendingAmount: number;           // Bet amount in SOL\n  pendingSide: \"green\" | \"red\" | null;\n  potentialPayout: number;         // Payout if this side wins\n  userOdds: number;                // % of pool user owns\n  \n  // User history\n  userHistory: UserRoundHistory[]; // Past rounds with bets\n  recentCandles: Candle[];         // Last 15 candles (1min OHLC)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Polling & Timing\n\n| Mechanism | Interval | Behavior |\n|-----------|----------|----------|\n| **Backend round poll** | 2000ms | `GET /closecall/current-round` |\n| **Candle progress tick** | 100ms | Updates progress bar & countdown |\n| **Pyth price subscription** | Real-time | Updates current price, triggers candle builder |\n| **User history load** | On wallet connect | `GET /closecall/history?limit=20` |\n\n---\n\n### Error Handling & Silent Failures\n\n1. **Backend unavailable**: Silent — no error message, just no round shown\n2. **Transaction rejected by user**: Error modal with message\n3. **Betting closed (race condition)**: Error: \"Betting window has closed. Wait for the next round.\"\n4. **Insufficient balance**: Error: \"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL to complete this transaction.\"\n5. **Network error**: Error: \"Network error. Please check your connection and try again.\"\n6. **Simulation failed**: Error: \"Transaction simulation failed. The round may no longer be open for bets.\"\n\nAll user-facing error messages come from `parseTransactionError()` in `CloseCallContext.tsx` (lines 207–243).\n\n---\n\n### Test Flow Examples\n\n**E2E: Connect → Bet → Wait → Result**\n1. Check `!connected` → click `.close-call-action-btn` (Connect Wallet)\n2. Wait for wallet modal → confirm connection\n3. Check `currentRound !== null` (polling started)\n4. Check `.close-call-chart__label--betting` visible (betting open)\n5. Input amount: `.close-call-bet-input__field` = \"0.1\"\n6. Click `.close-call-side-btn--green`\n7. Wait for `.close-call-side-btn__label` to show \"Joining...\" → success\n8. Wait `currentRound.bettingEndsAt` to pass\n9. Check `.close-call-chart__label--locked` visible\n10. Wait for new round or `completedRound` to render\n11. Check `.close-call-main__banner` or `.RoundResultBanner` for outcome\n\n**E2E: Backend Down**\n1. Stop backend (kill `/closecall/current-round` endpoint)\n2. Load `/close-call`\n3. Expect: `.close-call-main__loading` visible for 2s, then hides\n4. No error message shown — silent fallback\n\n**E2E: Round Details Page**\n1. Complete a bet\n2. Click history entry\n3. Modal opens → Click \"View Round Details →\" link\n4. Navigate to `/close-call/{roundId}`\n5. Fetch `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/{roundId}`\n6. Expect: Pool info, entries, settlement details (if settled)\n\n---\n\nThis reference covers all the major DOM structures, classes, selectors, and context states you'll need for comprehensive E2E test coverage of the Close Call frontend."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a870401ecb3b284d5 (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 63834\ntool_uses: 9\nduration_ms: 60518</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1de1cbce-bcf6-4659-9a0e-c65f55d25303","uuid":"34716b59-b002-4d3f-9855-51df9521f132","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Read these files for the Close Call frontend:\n\n1. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/features/close-call/context/CloseCallContext.tsx`\n2. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallPage.tsx`\n3. `sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/src/pages/CloseCallRoundPage.tsx`\n\nI need to understand:\n- How the frontend displays round state\n- What UI elements show when wallet is connected vs disconnected\n- What happens when backend is available vs unavailable\n- DOM selectors I can use in E2E tests (data-testid, text content, CSS classes)","agentId":"a870401ecb3b284d5","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Now let me compile a comprehensive summary of the Close Call frontend structure with DOM selectors for E2E testing. Here's my analysis:\n\n---\n\n## Close Call Frontend: Complete DOM & State Reference\n\n### Architecture Overview\n\n**Key Context Providers:**\n- `CloseCallContext` (from `/CloseCallContext.tsx`) — manages round state, betting, price subscription, and on-chain interaction\n- `CloseCallProvider` wraps the content and provides context via `useCloseCall()` hook\n\n**Page Structure:**\n- **`CloseCallPage.tsx`** — Main game page (renders `CloseCallPageContent` inside provider)\n- **`CloseCallRoundPage.tsx`** — Deep-link detail page for completed rounds (fetches from `/fairness/rounds/by-id/{roundId}`)\n\n---\n\n### Round State Visualization\n\n#### How Frontend Displays Round State\n\n| Round Phase | UI Indicators | Context State |\n|-------------|---------------|---------------|\n| **Initial Load** | Spinner + \"Loading chart...\" | `loading: true`, `currentRound: null` |\n| **Open (Betting)** | Chart visible, Bet buttons enabled, Progress bar white (0-10s) | `currentRound.phase: \"open\"`, `Date.now() < currentRound.bettingEndsAt` |\n| **Locked (No Betting)** | Chart visible, Bet buttons disabled, Progress bar gray (10-60s) | `currentRound.phase: \"open\"`, `Date.now() >= currentRound.bettingEndsAt` |\n| **Settled/Refunded** | Result banner visible, new round starts polling | `currentRound: null`, `completedRound: { outcome: \"green\" \\| \"red\" \\| \"refund\" }` |\n| **Backend Unavailable** | No round shown, no chart | `fetchCurrentRound()` returns `null`, `loading: true` (after retry) |\n\n---\n\n### Wallet Connection States\n\n#### Connected Wallet\n- **Sidebar buttons render:** `SideSelector` component with GREEN/RED buttons\n- **Bet amount input:** Enabled (unless user already bet or betting closed)\n- **Expected DOM:**\n  - Button with class `close-call-side-btn--green`\n  - Button with class `close-call-side-btn--red`\n  - Input with class `close-call-bet-input__field`\n\n#### Disconnected Wallet\n- **Single button rendered:** `<button className=\"close-call-action-btn\">Connect Wallet</button>`\n- **Clicking triggers:** `connect()` from wallet adapter\n- **Expected DOM:**\n  - Button containing text: \"Connect Wallet\"\n  - Class: `close-call-action-btn`\n\n---\n\n### Backend Availability States\n\n#### Backend Running (Healthy)\n- Polls `/closecall/current-round` every 2s (line 413)\n- If round exists: displays chart, pool, candles\n- If round settled: fetches `/fairness/rounds/by-id/{roundId}` to show completion\n- Expected: Round displays normally within 2s of load\n\n#### Backend Down / Unreachable\n- `fetchCurrentRound()` catches all errors → returns `null` (line 118)\n- Frontend shows: Empty state (no chart, no round data)\n- **Does NOT show error message** — silently falls back to null\n- Retries continue every 2s in background\n- Expected: No crash, just blank sidebar/main area until backend recovers\n\n**Note:** Error handling is silent by design. No error toast or error message shown to player if backend is unavailable initially.\n\n---\n\n### DOM Selectors for E2E Tests\n\n#### Main Page Structure\n```\n[Main Container]\n  .close-call-main                           # Main game area\n    .close-call-main__banner                 # \"Will the current candle close GREEN or RED?\"\n    .close-call-main__loading                # Shows when loading === true\n    .close-call-main__spinner                # Spinner div (child of loading)\n    [CandlestickChart]                       # Chart component (when not loading)\n\n[Sidebar]\n  .close-call-sidebar\n    .close-call-sidebar__section             # Multiple sections: input, buttons, pool, fairness info\n```\n\n#### Chart Component Selectors\n```\n.close-call-chart\n  .close-call-chart__header\n    .close-call-chart__asset-name            # Text: \"BTC/USD 1 min\"\n  .close-call-chart__container\n    .close-call-chart__lw-chart              # Lightweight Charts container (ref)\n    .close-call-chart__price-panel           # Right-side price display\n      .close-call-chart__current-price       # Colored current price (green/red)\n      .close-call-chart__ohl                 # O, H, L price rows\n  .close-call-chart__footer\n    .close-call-chart__progress              # Progress bar container\n      .close-call-chart__progress-fill--betting  # White fill (0-10s)\n      .close-call-chart__progress-fill--locked   # Gray fill (10-60s)\n    .close-call-chart__label\n      .close-call-chart__label--betting      # \"BETTING OPEN • Ns to bet\" (when open)\n      .close-call-chart__label--locked       # \"BETTING LOCKED • Candle Close in Ns\" (when locked)\n```\n\n#### Bet Amount Input Selectors\n```\n.close-call-bet-input\n  .close-call-bet-input__label               # \"Bet Amount ($)\"\n  .close-call-bet-input__field               # Input field (text, decimal mode)\n  .close-call-bet-input__btn                 # Adjustment buttons: ½, 2x, MAX\n  .close-call-bet-input__range               # \"Min: X  Max: Y\"\n\n[Disabled state]\n  .close-call-bet-input--disabled            # Applied to container when disabled\n```\n\n#### Side Selector (Bet Buttons) Selectors\n```\n.close-call-side-selector\n  .close-call-side-btn.close-call-side-btn--green\n    .close-call-side-btn__label              # Text: \"GREEN\" or \"Joining...\"\n  .close-call-side-btn.close-call-side-btn--red\n    .close-call-side-btn__label              # Text: \"RED\" or \"Joining...\"\n\n[Selected state]\n  .close-call-side-btn--selected             # Applied to active button\n\n[Disabled state]\n  .close-call-side-selector--disabled        # Applied to container\n```\n\n#### Pool Distribution Selectors\n```\n.close-call-pool-bar\n  .close-call-pool-bar__labels\n    .close-call-pool-bar__label--green       # Green %\n    .close-call-pool-bar__label--red         # Red %\n  .close-call-pool-bar__track\n    .close-call-pool-bar__fill--green        # Green pool width\n    .close-call-pool-bar__fill--red          # Red pool width\n  .close-call-pool-bar__stats\n    .close-call-pool-bar__pool-amount        # Pool SOL amounts\n    .close-call-pool-bar__odds               # Odds multiplier (~Nx)\n  .close-call-pool-bar__prize\n    .close-call-pool-bar__prize-label        # \"PRIZE POOL\"\n    .close-call-pool-bar__prize-amount\n      .close-call-pool-bar__prize-sol        # Total pool SOL display\n  \n  [User Bet Active]\n  .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet-header    # \"Joined GREEN\" or \"Joined RED\"\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet-row       # Amount row\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet-value     # \"X.XXXX SOL\"\n    \n    [If User Won]\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet--won      # Container modifier\n    .close-call-pool-bar__win-animation      # Star/coin animation\n    .close-call-pool-bar__stars              # Star elements\n    .close-call-pool-bar__coins              # Coin elements\n    \n    [If User Lost]\n    .close-call-pool-bar__user-bet--lost     # Container modifier\n    .close-call-pool-bar__loss-animation     # Heartbreak emoji animation\n```\n\n#### Result Banner Selectors\n```\n.close-call-main > [RoundResultBanner]       # Component from @rng-utopia/ui\n  [Rendered when completedRound !== null]\n  [Shows: \"GREEN WINS\" / \"RED WINS\" / \"REFUND\"]\n  [Shows: \"You Won!\" / \"You Lost\" / \"Bet refunded\" + payout amount]\n```\n\n#### History Modal Selectors\n```\n.close-call-history-modal\n  .close-call-history-modal__section         # Multiple sections: Stats, Candle Data, Oracle Verification\n  .close-call-history-modal__section-title   # Section headers\n  .close-call-history-modal__row              # Label/value pairs\n  .close-call-history-modal__hash            # Monospace hash display (copyable)\n  .close-call-history-modal__verify-link     # \"View Round Details →\" link to /close-call/{roundId}\n\n[History Entry List - from GameLayout]\n  .close-call-history-result                 # History row result display\n  .close-call-history-result__separator      # \"|\" separator\n```\n\n#### Payout Message Selectors (Completed Round)\n```\n.close-call-payout-received                  # Shows under pool when user won\n  .close-call-payout-received__label         # \"Payout Received!\"\n  .close-call-payout-received__amount        # \"+X.XXXX SOL\"\n```\n\n#### Fairness Info Selectors\n```\n.close-call-sidebar__fairness\n  .close-call-sidebar__fairness-title        # \"Round Info\"\n  .close-call-sidebar__fairness-row          # \"Round ID\" and \"Oracle\" rows\n  .close-call-sidebar__hash                  # Hash display (last 12 chars of roundId)\n```\n\n#### Round Details Page (`/close-call/{roundId}`)\n```\n[Main container: max-width 640px, centered]\n  [Back link] → \"/close-call\"\n  <h2>Close Call Round Details</h2>\n  \n  [Status section]\n    \"Round ID\", \"Status\", \"Created\"\n  \n  [Oracle Prices section]\n    \"Open Price\", \"Close Price\" (if settled), \"Outcome\" (if settled)\n  \n  [Pool section]\n    \"Green Pool\", \"Red Pool\", \"Total Pool\", \"Fee Collected\" (if settled)\n  \n  [Entries section]\n    GREEN entries list, RED entries list (with addresses and amounts)\n  \n  [Settlement section] (if settled)\n    \"Settled At\", \"Settlement Tx\", \"Price Source\", \"Resolution\"\n    Verification explanation paragraph (text color: #94a3b8)\n  \n  [Open Round message]\n    \"Round is still open. Outcome and close price will be available after settlement.\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### Context Hook Values (Key Selectors)\n\nFrom `useCloseCall()`, you can test:\n\n```typescript\n{\n  // Round data\n  currentRound: {\n    id: string;                    // e.g., \"0x1234...abcd\" (hex)\n    phase: \"open\" | \"settled\" | \"refunded\";\n    pool: { greenPool, redPool, totalPool, greenBets[], redBets[] };\n    outcome: \"green\" | \"red\" | \"refund\" | undefined;\n    bettingEndsAt: timestamp;\n  },\n  completedRound: Round | null,   // Previous round after settlement\n  \n  // Loading\n  loading: boolean;                // true on initial load, false after first poll\n  placingBet: boolean;             // true during tx send/confirm\n  \n  // User interaction\n  currentPrice: number;            // BTC price from Pyth\n  candleProgress: number;          // 0-1, progress through 60s candle\n  userBet: PlayerBet | null;       // User's active bet in current round\n  pendingAmount: number;           // Bet amount in SOL\n  pendingSide: \"green\" | \"red\" | null;\n  potentialPayout: number;         // Payout if this side wins\n  userOdds: number;                // % of pool user owns\n  \n  // User history\n  userHistory: UserRoundHistory[]; // Past rounds with bets\n  recentCandles: Candle[];         // Last 15 candles (1min OHLC)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n### Key Polling & Timing\n\n| Mechanism | Interval | Behavior |\n|-----------|----------|----------|\n| **Backend round poll** | 2000ms | `GET /closecall/current-round` |\n| **Candle progress tick** | 100ms | Updates progress bar & countdown |\n| **Pyth price subscription** | Real-time | Updates current price, triggers candle builder |\n| **User history load** | On wallet connect | `GET /closecall/history?limit=20` |\n\n---\n\n### Error Handling & Silent Failures\n\n1. **Backend unavailable**: Silent — no error message, just no round shown\n2. **Transaction rejected by user**: Error modal with message\n3. **Betting closed (race condition)**: Error: \"Betting window has closed. Wait for the next round.\"\n4. **Insufficient balance**: Error: \"Insufficient balance. You need more SOL to complete this transaction.\"\n5. **Network error**: Error: \"Network error. Please check your connection and try again.\"\n6. **Simulation failed**: Error: \"Transaction simulation failed. The round may no longer be open for bets.\"\n\nAll user-facing error messages come from `parseTransactionError()` in `CloseCallContext.tsx` (lines 207–243).\n\n---\n\n### Test Flow Examples\n\n**E2E: Connect → Bet → Wait → Result**\n1. Check `!connected` → click `.close-call-action-btn` (Connect Wallet)\n2. Wait for wallet modal → confirm connection\n3. Check `currentRound !== null` (polling started)\n4. Check `.close-call-chart__label--betting` visible (betting open)\n5. Input amount: `.close-call-bet-input__field` = \"0.1\"\n6. Click `.close-call-side-btn--green`\n7. Wait for `.close-call-side-btn__label` to show \"Joining...\" → success\n8. Wait `currentRound.bettingEndsAt` to pass\n9. Check `.close-call-chart__label--locked` visible\n10. Wait for new round or `completedRound` to render\n11. Check `.close-call-main__banner` or `.RoundResultBanner` for outcome\n\n**E2E: Backend Down**\n1. Stop backend (kill `/closecall/current-round` endpoint)\n2. Load `/close-call`\n3. Expect: `.close-call-main__loading` visible for 2s, then hides\n4. No error message shown — silent fallback\n\n**E2E: Round Details Page**\n1. Complete a bet\n2. Click history entry\n3. Modal opens → Click \"View Round Details →\" link\n4. Navigate to `/close-call/{roundId}`\n5. Fetch `GET /fairness/rounds/by-id/{roundId}`\n6. Expect: Pool info, entries, settlement details (if settled)\n\n---\n\nThis reference covers all the major DOM structures, classes, selectors, and context states you'll need for comprehensive E2E test coverage of the Close Call frontend."}],"totalDurationMs":60518,"totalTokens":63834,"totalToolUseCount":9,"usage":{"input_tokens":5,"cache