{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01J4DkMj6TbDT24GtmVyAJQv","type":"tool_result","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive view of the devnet E2E test infrastructure. Let me create a detailed summary report.\n\n## Devnet E2E Test Infrastructure Report\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the RNG Utopia codebase, here's a comprehensive guide to the devnet E2E test patterns, architecture, and mechanics:\n\n---\n\n### **Overview & Architecture**\n\nThe devnet E2E tests are a two-tier system designed to validate the complete game lifecycle against **real deployed contracts** on Solana devnet with **live fairness backend settlement**:\n\n1. **Frontend (Playwright)**: Two isolated browser contexts simulating Player A and Player B\n2. **On-chain (Solana RPC)**: Real devnet contracts for Coinflip and Lord of RNGs\n3. **Backend (Fairness Service)**: Live settlement engine that commits, reveals, calculates results, and executes on-chain payouts\n\n---\n\n### **File Locations**\n\n**Test specs**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/smoke.spec.ts` — Environment validation and app load\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts` — Full Coinflip E2E flow\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lord-lifecycle.spec.ts` — Full Lord of RNGs E2E flow\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/deeplink.spec.ts` — URL routing validation\n\n**Helper modules**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts` — Environment validation & program checks\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/retry.ts` — Retry/backoff logic for on-chain reads\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/wallets.ts` — Deterministic keypairs (Player A & B)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/on-chain-cleanup.ts` — Pre-flight match cleanup (Coinflip)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/lord-on-chain-cleanup.ts` — Pre-flight round cleanup (Lord)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/tx-utils.ts` — Signed transaction sending utilities\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts` — Playwright fixtures (dual-player contexts, connections)\n\n**Configuration**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.devnet.config.ts` — Playwright test config\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh` — Single entrypoint script for running tests\n\n---\n\n### **Environment Validation (`env.ts`)**\n\n**Required env vars** (fail-fast if missing):\n```\nVITE_RPC_URL              — Devnet RPC endpoint (https)\nVITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID  — Deployed coinflip program (base58)\nVITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID  — Deployed platform program (base58)\nVITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL — Running fairness backend base URL (http(s))\n```\n\n**Optional** (with defaults):\n```\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK      — Cluster name (default: \"devnet\")\nVITE_LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID — Lord of RNGs program (optional, skips if invalid)\n```\n\n**Validation flow** in `validateDevnetEnv()`:\n1. Check all required vars present (consolidate errors, throw early if missing)\n2. Parse and validate URLs (must be http/https, use `new URL()`)\n3. Parse and validate public keys (must be valid base58, throw on invalid)\n4. Return `DevnetConfig` object with validated values\n\n**Pre-flight checks** in `verifyDevnetDeployments()`:\n1. RPC health check via `getLatestBlockhash()`\n2. Verify Coinflip program is deployed and executable\n3. Verify Platform program is deployed and executable\n4. Verify Lord of RNGs program (if configured)\n5. Verify backend health via `GET /health` endpoint\n\n**Error strategy**: Fail fast with consolidated, human-readable error messages. Don't let tests proceed if environment is broken.\n\n---\n\n### **Retry & Backoff Mechanism (`retry.ts`)**\n\nSimple **fixed-delay retry** wrapper (`withRetry()`):\n\n```typescript\ninterface RetryOptions {\n  retries?: number;      // default: 3\n  delayMs?: number;      // default: 2_000ms (2 seconds)\n  label?: string;        // human-readable label for logs\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Attempt function up to N times with fixed delay between attempts\n- Log each attempt failure with elapsed time and error message\n- Re-throw last error if all attempts exhausted\n- Used for on-chain assertions that lag behind state changes (RPC eventually consistent)\n\n**Example usage**:\n```typescript\nconst { matchPda } = await withRetry(\n  () => assertMatchCreated(connection, PLAYER_A.publicKey, SIDE_HEADS, ENTRY_AMOUNT),\n  { label: \"assertMatchCreated\", retries: 10, delayMs: 1_000 }\n);\n```\n\n**No exponential backoff**: Fixed delay is simple and appropriate for RPC lag (typically 1-2 seconds).\n\n---\n\n### **Dual-Player Fixtures (`fixtures.ts`)**\n\n**Fixture setup**:\n```typescript\ninterface DevnetDualPlayerFixtures {\n  devnetConfig: DevnetConfig;           // Validated env config\n  playerAContext: BrowserContext;       // Isolated browser context\n  playerBContext: BrowserContext;       // Isolated browser context\n  playerAPage: Page;                    // Page in Player A's context\n  playerBPage: Page;                    // Page in Player B's context\n  playerAKeypair: Keypair;              // Deterministic keypair\n  playerBKeypair: Keypair;              // Deterministic keypair\n  connection: Connection;               // Shared RPC connection\n}\n```\n\n**Key mechanisms**:\n1. **Keypair injection**: Each player's keypair is injected via `addInitScript()` into the browser context as `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n   - 32-byte seed converted to array, passed to browser context\n   - TestWalletProvider reads this seed and creates a deterministic wallet\n2. **Isolated contexts**: Player A and B cannot interfere with each other (separate localStorage, cookies, etc.)\n3. **Shared connection**: Both players use the same RPC connection (configurable commitment: \"confirmed\")\n4. **Connection timeout**: 120 seconds for transaction confirmation\n\n---\n\n### **Deterministic Test Wallets (`wallets.ts`)**\n\nTwo hardcoded deterministic keypairs derived from fixed 32-byte seeds:\n\n```typescript\nconst SEED_PLAYER_A = new Uint8Array([249, 96, 168, 181, 111, ...])  // 32 bytes\nconst SEED_PLAYER_B = new Uint8Array([131, 192, 135, 198, 45, ...])  // 32 bytes\n\nexport const PLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_A);\nexport const PLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_B);\n```\n\n**Benefits**:\n- Reproducible across test runs (same address every time)\n- Easy to identify stale on-chain state between runs\n- Can pre-fund wallets on devnet (manual airdrop)\n- No need to generate fresh keypairs per test\n\n**Devnet funding requirement**: Each wallet must have **≥ 0.1 SOL** before tests run (minimum balance check in `ensureFunded()`).\n\n---\n\n### **On-Chain Pre-Flight Cleanup**\n\n#### **Coinflip Cleanup** (`on-chain-cleanup.ts`)\n\n**Problem**: Deterministic wallets share match PDAs across runs. Stale matches from failed tests block new match creation.\n\n**Solution**: Check and clean stale match PDAs before each test.\n\n**State machine**:\n```\ncheckMatchState(creator) → \n  phase: \"waiting\" | \"locked\" | null\n\nIf null (no match):        → CLEAN, return\nIf \"waiting\" (not locked):  → sendCleanupTx(cancelMatch)\nIf \"locked\" + deadline OK:  → sendCleanupTx(timeoutRefund)\nIf \"locked\" + not expired:  → throw \"Settlement in-flight\"\n```\n\n**Key flow** in `ensureCleanState()`:\n1. Call `checkMatchState()` to find active match PDA via memcmp filter (offset=8, search by creator address)\n2. If no match → clean\n3. If \"waiting\" → build `cancelMatch` instruction\n4. If \"locked\" → check resolve deadline:\n   - If deadline passed → build `timeoutRefund` instruction\n   - If not passed → throw error (settlement in-flight, user should wait or rerun later)\n5. Send signed TX, confirm, verify match PDA gone\n6. Retry up to 2 times with 3-second delay\n\n**Transaction helper** (`sendSignedTx()` in `tx-utils.ts`):\n- Build TX with latest blockhash and lastValidBlockHeight\n- Sign with creator keypair\n- Send with `skipPreflight: false, preflightCommitment: \"confirmed\"`\n- Confirm via `confirmTransaction()`\n- Return signature\n- **Does NOT blindly retry**: Caller re-checks on-chain state to determine if TX actually landed\n\n#### **Lord of RNGs Cleanup** (`lord-on-chain-cleanup.ts`)\n\n**Different model**: Lord rounds don't have a user-facing cancel. Cleanup uses:\n1. **`timeout_refund`**: Player can call after resolve deadline expires (refunds all players)\n2. **`force_close`**: Admin can call anytime to clean expired rounds\n3. **Authority keypair**: Loaded from `~/.config/solana/id.json`, cached for admin operations\n\n**State machine**:\n```\nfindPlayerRounds(player) →\n  phase: \"waiting\" | \"active\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\"\n\nIf no rounds:           → CLEAN\nIf \"active\" + deadline OK: → timeoutRefund\nIf \"waiting\" or \"active\" + no deadline: \n  If authority available  → forceClose\n  Else                    → throw \"Settlement in-flight\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Test Patterns & Assertions**\n\n#### **Smoke Test** (`smoke.spec.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Validate environment before running expensive lifecycle tests.\n\n**What it checks**:\n1. Devnet deployments reachable (RPC health + program existence)\n2. App loads without blank screen\n3. Wallet connects (test keypair auto-injected)\n\n**No VRF fulfillment required** — fast (~1 minute).\n\n#### **Coinflip Lifecycle** (`lifecycle.spec.ts`)\n\n**Full flow**:\n```\n[Setup] Fund wallets, clean stale matches\n[Phase 1] Player A creates match (onchain + backend)\n[Phase 2] Player B joins match (ui + onchain)\n[Phase 3] Backend settles (commit-reveal, on-chain payout)\n[Phase 4] Both players see result, verify treasury fee\n```\n\n**Key assertions**:\n1. **On-chain match creation** (`assertMatchCreated`):\n   - Match PDA exists at expected address (seeds: [\"match\", creator, match_id])\n   - Phase is \"waiting\"\n   - Entry amount matches wager\n2. **Backend round creation** (via `GET /fairness/rounds/{pda}`):\n   - Round exists in \"created\" phase\n   - Commitment is valid hex (SHA256)\n   - Secret is undefined (not yet revealed)\n3. **Settlement** (polling with 2-second intervals):\n   - Backend phase → \"settled\"\n   - Winner is one of the two players (predictable from result_side)\n   - Secret and resultHash are revealed (valid hex)\n4. **UI updates** (player sees \"won\" or \"lost\"):\n   - Active match view shows result\n   - Both players return to lobby or stay on result\n5. **On-chain closure** (`assertMatchClosed`):\n   - Match PDA is closed (rent refunded)\n   - Verified with retry (may lag 1-2 seconds)\n6. **Treasury fee** (`assertTreasuryFee`):\n   - Treasury account balance increased by expected 3%\n   - Verified with retry\n\n**WebSocket settlement events**:\n- Tests capture console logs with \"[settlement-event]\" marker\n- Expect at least one \"subscribed\" log (subscription active)\n- Optional: \"matched\" log (WS beats polling)\n- Warning if polling wins the race (WS is slower)\n\n**Console error filtering**:\n- Define `DEVNET_NOISE_PATTERNS` to ignore known harmless errors:\n  - \"favicon.ico\", \"third-party cookie\", \"429\", \"WebSocket\", \"ECONNRESET\", etc.\n- Filter devnet-specific errors: `filterDevnetNoise()`\n- Expect zero real errors at end\n\n**Timeout**: 300 seconds (accounts for VRF fulfillment delays)\n\n#### **Lord of RNGs Lifecycle** (`lord-lifecycle.spec.ts`)\n\n**Similar pattern** to Coinflip:\n```\n[Setup] Fund wallets, clean stale rounds\n[Phase 1] Player A starts round (UI)\n[Phase 2] Player B joins round (UI)\n[Phase 3] Backend settles (commit-reveal, payout tx)\n[Phase 4] Both players see settlement UI, verify treasury fee\n```\n\n**Key differences**:\n- Uses `JackpotRound` account (vs `CoinflipMatch`)\n- Finds round via program discriminator + player filter\n- Checks `round.phase` enum (not numeric phase code)\n- Waits for `totalAmountLamports` in backend response\n- Expects `winningEntryIndex` and `winningOffset` from entropy\n- Settlement event marker: \"[lord-of-rngs] settlement-event\"\n\n**Timeout**: 300 seconds (180+ for settlement)\n\n#### **Deeplink Test** (`deeplink.spec.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Verify URL updates when creating a match.\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Navigate to `/coinflip`\n2. Create a match\n3. Wait for URL to match `/coinflip/[0-9a-f]{16}` (match ID)\n4. Polls every 1 second with 15-second timeout\n\n---\n\n### **Test Runner Script** (`run-e2e-devnet.sh`)\n\n**Single entrypoint**: `bash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh [--grep pattern]`\n\n**What it does**:\n1. **Auto-source env files**: Checks `.env.local` then `.env.devnet`, fills gaps in environment\n2. **Ensure PostgreSQL**: Starts PG if not running (`pg_ctlcluster` or sudo)\n3. **Backend bootstrapping**:\n   - If backend `/health` is healthy → use existing\n   - Otherwise: run migrations, start new backend process\n4. **Env validation**: Fail-fast if required vars missing\n5. **Port cleanup**: Kill stale processes on port 3003 (Vite) and 3100 (backend)\n6. **Run Playwright**: `npx playwright test --config playwright.devnet.config.ts \"$@\"`\n\n**Exit codes**:\n- `0`: Tests passed\n- `1`: Environment broken, backend failed, or test failed\n\n**Database setup**: \n- Requires `DATABASE_URL` and `SERVER_KEYPAIR` env vars\n- Runs `pnpm --filter @rng-utopia/backend migrate` before starting\n- Tables created: users, challenges, rounds, treasury logs, etc.\n\n---\n\n### **Playwright Configuration** (`playwright.devnet.config.ts`)\n\n**Key settings**:\n```typescript\ntestDir: \"./e2e\"\nfullyParallel: false        // Sequential, not parallel\nworkers: 1                   // Single worker\nretries: 2                   // Retry failed tests\ntimeout: 300_000             // 300 second timeout per test\nbaseURL: \"http://localhost:3003\"\n\nwebServer: {\n  command: \"npx vite --port 3003\"\n  reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI\n  env: {\n    VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"  // Use real RPC, not mocks\n    VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\" // Use test wallet provider\n  }\n}\n\nscreenshot: \"only-on-failure\"\ntrace: \"retain-on-failure\"\nvideo: \"on\"\n```\n\n**Test matching**: Only runs `devnet/**/*.spec.ts` files\n\n---\n\n### **Error Handling & Diagnostics**\n\n**Console capture**:\n```typescript\nfunction capturePageDiagnostics(page: Page, sink: string[]) {\n  page.on(\"console\", (msg) => {\n    if (msg.type() === \"error\" || msg.text().includes(\"[coinflip]\")) {\n      sink.push(`[${msg.type()}] ${msg.text()}`);\n    }\n  });\n  page.on(\"pageerror\", (err) => {\n    sink.push(`[pageerror] ${err.message}`);\n  });\n}\n```\n\n**Polling patterns**:\n```typescript\nasync function waitForSettledRound(config, matchPda) {\n  const start = Date.now();\n  while (Date.now() - start < SETTLEMENT_TIMEOUT_MS) {\n    const round = await fetchBackendRound(config, matchPda);\n    if (round?.phase === \"settled\" && round.secret && round.settleTx) {\n      return round;\n    }\n    await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 2_000));  // Fixed 2-second delay\n  }\n  throw new Error(`Timed out waiting for backend to settle round ${matchPda}`);\n}\n```\n\n**Assertion patterns with retry**:\n```typescript\nawait withRetry(\n  () => assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda),\n  { label: \"assertMatchClosed\", retries: 8, delayMs: 2_000 }\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Key Constants & Timeouts**\n\n| Constant | Value | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `MIN_BALANCE_SOL` | 0.1 | Min wallet balance for tests |\n| `ENTRY_AMOUNT` | 5,000,000 lamports (0.005 SOL) | Default test wager |\n| `SETTLEMENT_TIMEOUT_MS` | 120,000 (Coinflip) / 180,000 (Lord) | Max time for backend settlement |\n| `DEVNET_NOISE_PATTERNS` | Array of strings | Known harmless errors to ignore |\n| Retry default: `retries=3, delayMs=2_000` | — | For on-chain reads |\n| Playwright timeout | 300,000 ms | Per-test timeout (includes VRF wait) |\n| RPC commitment | \"confirmed\" | Finality level for on-chain reads |\n\n---\n\n### **Common Failure Modes & Recovery**\n\n| Problem | Root Cause | Solution |\n|---------|-----------|----------|\n| \"VITE_RPC_URL is required\" | Env var missing | Export or set in `.env.devnet` |\n| \"Cannot reach devnet RPC\" | RPC endpoint down or blocked | Check RPC health, try different endpoint |\n| \"Coinflip program not found\" | Program not deployed | Deploy with `anchor deploy` or wait for deployment |\n| \"Timed out waiting for backend to settle\" | Backend not running or overloaded | Check `/health` endpoint, restart backend |\n| \"Settlement in-flight\" | Stale match not yet expired | Wait for deadline or rerun tests later |\n| \"VRF in-flight\" | Old test left VRF request pending | Wait 2-3 minutes or manually cleanup on-chain |\n| 401/429 console errors | Expected rate-limiting on devnet | Harmless, filtered by `DEVNET_NOISE_PATTERNS` |\n| \"match PDA persists despite tx error\" | TX didn't actually land | Check RPC state, may need manual cleanup |\n\n---\n\n### **Best Practices Observed**\n\n1. **Env validation before anything else**: `validateDevnetEnv()` called in every test's `beforeAll`\n2. **Deterministic wallets**: Same keypairs every run, easy to pre-fund and identify stale state\n3. **Fixed-delay retry**: Simple, predictable, appropriate for RPC lag\n4. **Pre-flight cleanup**: Ensures tests can run back-to-back without manual cleanup\n5. **Console filtering**: Separate signal from devnet noise, catch real errors\n6. **Polling over WebSocket**: Primary settlement detection is polling, WS is optional bonus\n7. **No blind retries**: Tx sending doesn't retry blindly; caller re-checks on-chain state\n8. **Consolidated error messages**: Users get actionable feedback, not raw errors\n9. **Separate fixtures for each game**: Coinflip and Lord have separate cleanup logic\n10. **Circuit breaker for \"in-flight\"**: Don't force-clean locked matches; surface the blocker\n\n---\n\n### **Testing This Locally**\n\n```bash\n# Setup\nexport VITE_RPC_URL=\"https://api.devnet.solana.com\"\nexport VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=\"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"\nexport VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=\"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"\nexport DATABASE_URL=\"postgresql://user:pass@localhost/rng_utopia\"\nexport SERVER_KEYPAIR=\"[1,2,3,...]\"\n\n# Run smoke test only (fast)\nbash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh --grep \"smoke\"\n\n# Run Coinflip lifecycle\nbash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh --grep \"coinflip devnet lifecycle\"\n\n# Run all devnet tests\nbash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh\n\n# Debug: capture screenshots + traces\nbash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh --grep \"lifecycle\"\n# Check: test-results/ for .png, .webm, .zip traces\n```\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive infrastructure enables **reliable, reproducible E2E testing** against real devnet contracts with deterministic wallets, robust retry logic, and clear error diagnostics."},{"type":"text","text":"agentId: a0f42f5e0e02d027a (for resuming to continue this agent's work if needed)\n<usage>total_tokens: 71789\ntool_uses: 20\nduration_ms: 106020</usage>"}]}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1de1cbce-bcf6-4659-9a0e-c65f55d25303","uuid":"82acb2ec-7571-4dac-9df7-bbd8f2fb469b","tool_use_result":{"status":"completed","prompt":"Find and read all devnet E2E test files in the repository. I need to understand the test patterns, env validation, retry/backoff mechanisms, and how they interact with real backends and on-chain programs.\n\nLook in:\n1. `apps/platform/e2e/devnet/` or similar directories for devnet E2E tests\n2. Any test config or fixtures related to devnet E2E\n3. The reference memory at `/home/vscode/.claude/projects/-workspaces-rng-utopia/memory/reference_e2e_devnet.md`\n\nRead the full contents of any devnet E2E test files you find. Also check for:\n- How env validation is done\n- How retry/backoff works\n- What assertions are made\n- How the tests interact with the backend API and on-chain state\n- What Playwright helpers/fixtures are used","agentId":"a0f42f5e0e02d027a","content":[{"type":"text","text":"Excellent! Now I have a comprehensive view of the devnet E2E test infrastructure. Let me create a detailed summary report.\n\n## Devnet E2E Test Infrastructure Report\n\nBased on my thorough analysis of the RNG Utopia codebase, here's a comprehensive guide to the devnet E2E test patterns, architecture, and mechanics:\n\n---\n\n### **Overview & Architecture**\n\nThe devnet E2E tests are a two-tier system designed to validate the complete game lifecycle against **real deployed contracts** on Solana devnet with **live fairness backend settlement**:\n\n1. **Frontend (Playwright)**: Two isolated browser contexts simulating Player A and Player B\n2. **On-chain (Solana RPC)**: Real devnet contracts for Coinflip and Lord of RNGs\n3. **Backend (Fairness Service)**: Live settlement engine that commits, reveals, calculates results, and executes on-chain payouts\n\n---\n\n### **File Locations**\n\n**Test specs**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/smoke.spec.ts` — Environment validation and app load\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lifecycle.spec.ts` — Full Coinflip E2E flow\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lord-lifecycle.spec.ts` — Full Lord of RNGs E2E flow\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/deeplink.spec.ts` — URL routing validation\n\n**Helper modules**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/env.ts` — Environment validation & program checks\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/retry.ts` — Retry/backoff logic for on-chain reads\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/wallets.ts` — Deterministic keypairs (Player A & B)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/on-chain-cleanup.ts` — Pre-flight match cleanup (Coinflip)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/lord-on-chain-cleanup.ts` — Pre-flight round cleanup (Lord)\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/helpers/tx-utils.ts` — Signed transaction sending utilities\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/fixtures.ts` — Playwright fixtures (dual-player contexts, connections)\n\n**Configuration**:\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/playwright.devnet.config.ts` — Playwright test config\n- `/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh` — Single entrypoint script for running tests\n\n---\n\n### **Environment Validation (`env.ts`)**\n\n**Required env vars** (fail-fast if missing):\n```\nVITE_RPC_URL              — Devnet RPC endpoint (https)\nVITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID  — Deployed coinflip program (base58)\nVITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID  — Deployed platform program (base58)\nVITE_FAIRNESS_BACKEND_URL — Running fairness backend base URL (http(s))\n```\n\n**Optional** (with defaults):\n```\nVITE_SOLANA_NETWORK      — Cluster name (default: \"devnet\")\nVITE_LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID — Lord of RNGs program (optional, skips if invalid)\n```\n\n**Validation flow** in `validateDevnetEnv()`:\n1. Check all required vars present (consolidate errors, throw early if missing)\n2. Parse and validate URLs (must be http/https, use `new URL()`)\n3. Parse and validate public keys (must be valid base58, throw on invalid)\n4. Return `DevnetConfig` object with validated values\n\n**Pre-flight checks** in `verifyDevnetDeployments()`:\n1. RPC health check via `getLatestBlockhash()`\n2. Verify Coinflip program is deployed and executable\n3. Verify Platform program is deployed and executable\n4. Verify Lord of RNGs program (if configured)\n5. Verify backend health via `GET /health` endpoint\n\n**Error strategy**: Fail fast with consolidated, human-readable error messages. Don't let tests proceed if environment is broken.\n\n---\n\n### **Retry & Backoff Mechanism (`retry.ts`)**\n\nSimple **fixed-delay retry** wrapper (`withRetry()`):\n\n```typescript\ninterface RetryOptions {\n  retries?: number;      // default: 3\n  delayMs?: number;      // default: 2_000ms (2 seconds)\n  label?: string;        // human-readable label for logs\n}\n```\n\n**Behavior**:\n- Attempt function up to N times with fixed delay between attempts\n- Log each attempt failure with elapsed time and error message\n- Re-throw last error if all attempts exhausted\n- Used for on-chain assertions that lag behind state changes (RPC eventually consistent)\n\n**Example usage**:\n```typescript\nconst { matchPda } = await withRetry(\n  () => assertMatchCreated(connection, PLAYER_A.publicKey, SIDE_HEADS, ENTRY_AMOUNT),\n  { label: \"assertMatchCreated\", retries: 10, delayMs: 1_000 }\n);\n```\n\n**No exponential backoff**: Fixed delay is simple and appropriate for RPC lag (typically 1-2 seconds).\n\n---\n\n### **Dual-Player Fixtures (`fixtures.ts`)**\n\n**Fixture setup**:\n```typescript\ninterface DevnetDualPlayerFixtures {\n  devnetConfig: DevnetConfig;           // Validated env config\n  playerAContext: BrowserContext;       // Isolated browser context\n  playerBContext: BrowserContext;       // Isolated browser context\n  playerAPage: Page;                    // Page in Player A's context\n  playerBPage: Page;                    // Page in Player B's context\n  playerAKeypair: Keypair;              // Deterministic keypair\n  playerBKeypair: Keypair;              // Deterministic keypair\n  connection: Connection;               // Shared RPC connection\n}\n```\n\n**Key mechanisms**:\n1. **Keypair injection**: Each player's keypair is injected via `addInitScript()` into the browser context as `window.__TEST_WALLET_SEED__`\n   - 32-byte seed converted to array, passed to browser context\n   - TestWalletProvider reads this seed and creates a deterministic wallet\n2. **Isolated contexts**: Player A and B cannot interfere with each other (separate localStorage, cookies, etc.)\n3. **Shared connection**: Both players use the same RPC connection (configurable commitment: \"confirmed\")\n4. **Connection timeout**: 120 seconds for transaction confirmation\n\n---\n\n### **Deterministic Test Wallets (`wallets.ts`)**\n\nTwo hardcoded deterministic keypairs derived from fixed 32-byte seeds:\n\n```typescript\nconst SEED_PLAYER_A = new Uint8Array([249, 96, 168, 181, 111, ...])  // 32 bytes\nconst SEED_PLAYER_B = new Uint8Array([131, 192, 135, 198, 45, ...])  // 32 bytes\n\nexport const PLAYER_A = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_A);\nexport const PLAYER_B = Keypair.fromSeed(SEED_PLAYER_B);\n```\n\n**Benefits**:\n- Reproducible across test runs (same address every time)\n- Easy to identify stale on-chain state between runs\n- Can pre-fund wallets on devnet (manual airdrop)\n- No need to generate fresh keypairs per test\n\n**Devnet funding requirement**: Each wallet must have **≥ 0.1 SOL** before tests run (minimum balance check in `ensureFunded()`).\n\n---\n\n### **On-Chain Pre-Flight Cleanup**\n\n#### **Coinflip Cleanup** (`on-chain-cleanup.ts`)\n\n**Problem**: Deterministic wallets share match PDAs across runs. Stale matches from failed tests block new match creation.\n\n**Solution**: Check and clean stale match PDAs before each test.\n\n**State machine**:\n```\ncheckMatchState(creator) → \n  phase: \"waiting\" | \"locked\" | null\n\nIf null (no match):        → CLEAN, return\nIf \"waiting\" (not locked):  → sendCleanupTx(cancelMatch)\nIf \"locked\" + deadline OK:  → sendCleanupTx(timeoutRefund)\nIf \"locked\" + not expired:  → throw \"Settlement in-flight\"\n```\n\n**Key flow** in `ensureCleanState()`:\n1. Call `checkMatchState()` to find active match PDA via memcmp filter (offset=8, search by creator address)\n2. If no match → clean\n3. If \"waiting\" → build `cancelMatch` instruction\n4. If \"locked\" → check resolve deadline:\n   - If deadline passed → build `timeoutRefund` instruction\n   - If not passed → throw error (settlement in-flight, user should wait or rerun later)\n5. Send signed TX, confirm, verify match PDA gone\n6. Retry up to 2 times with 3-second delay\n\n**Transaction helper** (`sendSignedTx()` in `tx-utils.ts`):\n- Build TX with latest blockhash and lastValidBlockHeight\n- Sign with creator keypair\n- Send with `skipPreflight: false, preflightCommitment: \"confirmed\"`\n- Confirm via `confirmTransaction()`\n- Return signature\n- **Does NOT blindly retry**: Caller re-checks on-chain state to determine if TX actually landed\n\n#### **Lord of RNGs Cleanup** (`lord-on-chain-cleanup.ts`)\n\n**Different model**: Lord rounds don't have a user-facing cancel. Cleanup uses:\n1. **`timeout_refund`**: Player can call after resolve deadline expires (refunds all players)\n2. **`force_close`**: Admin can call anytime to clean expired rounds\n3. **Authority keypair**: Loaded from `~/.config/solana/id.json`, cached for admin operations\n\n**State machine**:\n```\nfindPlayerRounds(player) →\n  phase: \"waiting\" | \"active\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\"\n\nIf no rounds:           → CLEAN\nIf \"active\" + deadline OK: → timeoutRefund\nIf \"waiting\" or \"active\" + no deadline: \n  If authority available  → forceClose\n  Else                    → throw \"Settlement in-flight\"\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Test Patterns & Assertions**\n\n#### **Smoke Test** (`smoke.spec.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Validate environment before running expensive lifecycle tests.\n\n**What it checks**:\n1. Devnet deployments reachable (RPC health + program existence)\n2. App loads without blank screen\n3. Wallet connects (test keypair auto-injected)\n\n**No VRF fulfillment required** — fast (~1 minute).\n\n#### **Coinflip Lifecycle** (`lifecycle.spec.ts`)\n\n**Full flow**:\n```\n[Setup] Fund wallets, clean stale matches\n[Phase 1] Player A creates match (onchain + backend)\n[Phase 2] Player B joins match (ui + onchain)\n[Phase 3] Backend settles (commit-reveal, on-chain payout)\n[Phase 4] Both players see result, verify treasury fee\n```\n\n**Key assertions**:\n1. **On-chain match creation** (`assertMatchCreated`):\n   - Match PDA exists at expected address (seeds: [\"match\", creator, match_id])\n   - Phase is \"waiting\"\n   - Entry amount matches wager\n2. **Backend round creation** (via `GET /fairness/rounds/{pda}`):\n   - Round exists in \"created\" phase\n   - Commitment is valid hex (SHA256)\n   - Secret is undefined (not yet revealed)\n3. **Settlement** (polling with 2-second intervals):\n   - Backend phase → \"settled\"\n   - Winner is one of the two players (predictable from result_side)\n   - Secret and resultHash are revealed (valid hex)\n4. **UI updates** (player sees \"won\" or \"lost\"):\n   - Active match view shows result\n   - Both players return to lobby or stay on result\n5. **On-chain closure** (`assertMatchClosed`):\n   - Match PDA is closed (rent refunded)\n   - Verified with retry (may lag 1-2 seconds)\n6. **Treasury fee** (`assertTreasuryFee`):\n   - Treasury account balance increased by expected 3%\n   - Verified with retry\n\n**WebSocket settlement events**:\n- Tests capture console logs with \"[settlement-event]\" marker\n- Expect at least one \"subscribed\" log (subscription active)\n- Optional: \"matched\" log (WS beats polling)\n- Warning if polling wins the race (WS is slower)\n\n**Console error filtering**:\n- Define `DEVNET_NOISE_PATTERNS` to ignore known harmless errors:\n  - \"favicon.ico\", \"third-party cookie\", \"429\", \"WebSocket\", \"ECONNRESET\", etc.\n- Filter devnet-specific errors: `filterDevnetNoise()`\n- Expect zero real errors at end\n\n**Timeout**: 300 seconds (accounts for VRF fulfillment delays)\n\n#### **Lord of RNGs Lifecycle** (`lord-lifecycle.spec.ts`)\n\n**Similar pattern** to Coinflip:\n```\n[Setup] Fund wallets, clean stale rounds\n[Phase 1] Player A starts round (UI)\n[Phase 2] Player B joins round (UI)\n[Phase 3] Backend settles (commit-reveal, payout tx)\n[Phase 4] Both players see settlement UI, verify treasury fee\n```\n\n**Key differences**:\n- Uses `JackpotRound` account (vs `CoinflipMatch`)\n- Finds round via program discriminator + player filter\n- Checks `round.phase` enum (not numeric phase code)\n- Waits for `totalAmountLamports` in backend response\n- Expects `winningEntryIndex` and `winningOffset` from entropy\n- Settlement event marker: \"[lord-of-rngs] settlement-event\"\n\n**Timeout**: 300 seconds (180+ for settlement)\n\n#### **Deeplink Test** (`deeplink.spec.ts`)\n\n**Purpose**: Verify URL updates when creating a match.\n\n**Flow**:\n1. Navigate to `/coinflip`\n2. Create a match\n3. Wait for URL to match `/coinflip/[0-9a-f]{16}` (match ID)\n4. Polls every 1 second with 15-second timeout\n\n---\n\n### **Test Runner Script** (`run-e2e-devnet.sh`)\n\n**Single entrypoint**: `bash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh [--grep pattern]`\n\n**What it does**:\n1. **Auto-source env files**: Checks `.env.local` then `.env.devnet`, fills gaps in environment\n2. **Ensure PostgreSQL**: Starts PG if not running (`pg_ctlcluster` or sudo)\n3. **Backend bootstrapping**:\n   - If backend `/health` is healthy → use existing\n   - Otherwise: run migrations, start new backend process\n4. **Env validation**: Fail-fast if required vars missing\n5. **Port cleanup**: Kill stale processes on port 3003 (Vite) and 3100 (backend)\n6. **Run Playwright**: `npx playwright test --config playwright.devnet.config.ts \"$@\"`\n\n**Exit codes**:\n- `0`: Tests passed\n- `1`: Environment broken, backend failed, or test failed\n\n**Database setup**: \n- Requires `DATABASE_URL` and `SERVER_KEYPAIR` env vars\n- Runs `pnpm --filter @rng-utopia/backend migrate` before starting\n- Tables created: users, challenges, rounds, treasury logs, etc.\n\n---\n\n### **Playwright Configuration** (`playwright.devnet.config.ts`)\n\n**Key settings**:\n```typescript\ntestDir: \"./e2e\"\nfullyParallel: false        // Sequential, not parallel\nworkers: 1                   // Single worker\nretries: 2                   // Retry failed tests\ntimeout: 300_000             // 300 second timeout per test\nbaseURL: \"http://localhost:3003\"\n\nwebServer: {\n  command: \"npx vite --port 3003\"\n  reuseExistingServer: !process.env.CI\n  env: {\n    VITE_MOCK_MODE: \"false\"  // Use real RPC, not mocks\n    VITE_TEST_WALLET: \"true\" // Use test wallet provider\n  }\n}\n\nscreenshot: \"only-on-failure\"\ntrace: \"retain-on-failure\"\nvideo: \"on\"\n```\n\n**Test matching**: Only runs `devnet/**/*.spec.ts` files\n\n---\n\n### **Error Handling & Diagnostics**\n\n**Console capture**:\n```typescript\nfunction capturePageDiagnostics(page: Page, sink: string[]) {\n  page.on(\"console\", (msg) => {\n    if (msg.type() === \"error\" || msg.text().includes(\"[coinflip]\")) {\n      sink.push(`[${msg.type()}] ${msg.text()}`);\n    }\n  });\n  page.on(\"pageerror\", (err) => {\n    sink.push(`[pageerror] ${err.message}`);\n  });\n}\n```\n\n**Polling patterns**:\n```typescript\nasync function waitForSettledRound(config, matchPda) {\n  const start = Date.now();\n  while (Date.now() - start < SETTLEMENT_TIMEOUT_MS) {\n    const round = await fetchBackendRound(config, matchPda);\n    if (round?.phase === \"settled\" && round.secret && round.settleTx) {\n      return round;\n    }\n    await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 2_000));  // Fixed 2-second delay\n  }\n  throw new Error(`Timed out waiting for backend to settle round ${matchPda}`);\n}\n```\n\n**Assertion patterns with retry**:\n```typescript\nawait withRetry(\n  () => assertMatchClosed(connection, matchPda),\n  { label: \"assertMatchClosed\", retries: 8, delayMs: 2_000 }\n);\n```\n\n---\n\n### **Key Constants & Timeouts**\n\n| Constant | Value | Purpose |\n|----------|-------|---------|\n| `MIN_BALANCE_SOL` | 0.1 | Min wallet balance for tests |\n| `ENTRY_AMOUNT` | 5,000,000 lamports (0.005 SOL) | Default test wager |\n| `SETTLEMENT_TIMEOUT_MS` | 120,000 (Coinflip) / 180,000 (Lord) | Max time for backend settlement |\n| `DEVNET_NOISE_PATTERNS` | Array of strings | Known harmless errors to ignore |\n| Retry default: `retries=3, delayMs=2_000` | — | For on-chain reads |\n| Playwright timeout | 300,000 ms | Per-test timeout (includes VRF wait) |\n| RPC commitment | \"confirmed\" | Finality level for on-chain reads |\n\n---\n\n### **Common Failure Modes & Recovery**\n\n| Problem | Root Cause | Solution |\n|---------|-----------|----------|\n| \"VITE_RPC_URL is required\" | Env var missing | Export or set in `.env.devnet` |\n| \"Cannot reach devnet RPC\" | RPC endpoint down or blocked | Check RPC health, try different endpoint |\n| \"Coinflip program not found\" | Program not deployed | Deploy with `anchor deploy` or wait for deployment |\n| \"Timed out waiting for backend to settle\" | Backend not running or overloaded | Check `/health` endpoint, restart backend |\n| \"Settlement in-flight\" | Stale match not yet expired | Wait for deadline or rerun tests later |\n| \"VRF in-flight\" | Old test left VRF request pending | Wait 2-3 minutes or manually cleanup on-chain |\n| 401/429 console errors | Expected rate-limiting on devnet | Harmless, filtered by `DEVNET_NOISE_PATTERNS` |\n| \"match PDA persists despite tx error\" | TX didn't actually land | Check RPC state, may need manual cleanup |\n\n---\n\n### **Best Practices Observed**\n\n1. **Env validation before anything else**: `validateDevnetEnv()` called in every test's `beforeAll`\n2. **Deterministic wallets**: Same keypairs every run, easy to pre-fund and identify stale state\n3. **Fixed-delay retry**: Simple, predictable, appropriate for RPC lag\n4. **Pre-flight cleanup**: Ensures tests can run back-to-back without manual cleanup\n5. **Console filtering**: Separate signal from devnet noise, catch real errors\n6. **Polling over WebSocket**: Primary settlement detection is polling, WS is optional bonus\n7. **No blind retries**: Tx sending doesn't retry blindly; caller re-checks on-chain state\n8. **Consolidated error messages**: Users get actionable feedback, not raw errors\n9. **Separate fixtures for each game**: Coinflip and Lord have separate cleanup logic\n10. **Circuit breaker for \"in-flight\"**: Don't force-clean locked matches; surface the blocker\n\n---\n\n### **Testing This Locally**\n\n```bash\n# Setup\nexport VITE_RPC_URL=\"https://api.devnet.solana.com\"\nexport VITE_COINFLIP_PROGRAM_ID=\"BdHFeqmkYe7znXV1Avk3zz496Pjo8QhEDN4MKPUTAWwx\"\nexport VITE_PLATFORM_PROGRAM_ID=\"85qwC1cDpSYkBBHUcN4nuZ119hCx4N94X38GjAHxnWjA\"\nexport DATABASE_URL=\"postgresql://user:pass@localhost/rng_utopia\"\nexport SERVER_KEYPAIR=\"[1,2,3,...]\"\n\n# Run smoke test only (fast)\nbash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh --grep \"smoke\"\n\n# Run Coinflip lifecycle\nbash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh --grep \"coinflip devnet lifecycle\"\n\n# Run all devnet tests\nbash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh\n\n# Debug: capture screenshots + traces\nbash scripts/run-e2e-devnet.sh --grep \"lifecycle\"\n# Check: test-results/ for .png, .webm, .zip traces\n```\n\n---\n\nThis comprehensive infrastructure enables **reliable, reproducible E2E testing** against real devnet contracts with deterministic wallets, robust retry logic, and clear error diagnostics."}],"totalDurationMs":106020,"totalTokens":71789,"totalToolUseCount":20,"usage":{"input_tokens":3,"cache_creation_input_tokens":562,"cache_read_input_tokens":65483,"output_tokens":5741,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":562},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_014n5KTdCLQ6Zyecbbyaaony","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of:\n\n1. The devnet E2E test patterns (dual-player fixtures, env validation, retry/backoff, console filtering, etc.)\n2. The Close Call backend API (endpoints, response shapes)\n3. The Close Call frontend (DOM selectors, states)\n\nThe checklist item says:\n```\n- [ ] [test] If external provider/oracle/VRF integration is in scope, add devnet real-provider E2E coverage in `e2e/devnet/**` with env validation + retry/backoff (or mark N/A with reason)\n```\n\nClose Call uses Pyth oracle, so external provider integration IS in scope. I need to add devnet E2E test coverage.\n\n\nSince Close Call rounds are backend-managed by the clock worker rather than player-initiated, the test needs to poll for an active round, then have both players place bets within the betting window before waiting for settlement at the next minute boundary. on GREEN\n4. Player B places bet on RED  \n5. Wait for settlement (poll backend API for settled state)\n6. Verify on-chain: round PDA closed (rent returned), treasury received fee\n7. Verify UI: both players see result\n\nBut wait — this is a complex flow that depends on:\n- Backend clock worker running and creating rounds\n- Pyth price data being fresh enough\n- The betting window being open when we try to bet\n\nLooking at the existing patterns more carefully, the devnet E2E tests for coinflip create a match via UI interaction (Player A), then Player B joins via UI. For Close Call, the flow is different:\n\n1. Backend creates round automatically\n2. Players bet within the 30s window\n3. Backend settles automatically\n\nThe key challenge is timing — we need to wait for a round to open, bet within the 30s window, then wait for settlement.\n\nI'm weighing three approaches here. A full lifecycle test would validate the entire flow but would be slow and flaky with Pyth oracle timing issues. A smoke-level test would just check that the environment is set up, the backend returns round data, and the UI loads correctly — much more reliable. Or I could mark it N/A since Pyth integration is in scope but the timing constraints make it impractical. Looking at the existing coinflip and lord lifecycle tests that run with 300s timeouts, I'm leaning toward the smoke-level approach as the most practical balance.\n\nNow I need to figure out what test files to create. I can see the existing structure has separate files for smoke tests, lifecycle tests, and deeplink tests, plus helper utilities for environment validation.\n\nFor Close Call, I'll need to update the environment validation to include the program ID, create a new lifecycle test file, and possibly add on-chain helpers. But the tricky part is that Close Call works differently—rounds are generated by a backend worker rather than player actions, and settlement happens automatically, so the test structure will need to account for that.\n\nThe practical approach is to have the test validate the environment and backend health, poll for an open round, have two players place bets through the UI on different outcomes, wait for settlement through API polling, and then verify both players see the result. Actually, I'm realizing the more reliable strategy is to focus on what the test can actually control—placing bets and verifying the UI reflects the outcome—rather than trying to orchestrate the entire round lifecycle.\n\nThe test should validate the environment setup, wait for a round to be available from the backend, have both players place opposing bets, then poll for settlement and verify the payouts are correct. The backend's clock worker should handle round creation and settlement automatically when the script runs, so the test just needs to work with whatever round state exists.\n\nBut there's a real timing issue here — catching a round during its 30-second betting window is tricky, and on devnet the Pyth oracle updates so infrequently that the clock worker often fails to create rounds due to stale prices. This makes a full lifecycle test pretty unreliable on devnet. I should probably focus on a smoke-level test instead that validates the core integration without relying on perfect timing conditions. I'm settling on a pragmatic approach: create a devnet E2E test that validates the program deployment, Pyth price account accessibility, and API responsiveness, then gracefully handle Pyth staleness by skipping the betting lifecycle if no active rounds exist. Now I need to examine the existing test patterns in env.ts, fixtures.ts, and smoke.spec.ts to match the codebase conventions.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":5698,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6822,"cache_read_input_tokens":43142,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6822},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1de1cbce-bcf6-4659-9a0e-c65f55d25303","uuid":"73963d70-d0dc-40ec-a5c6-bec50e01adec"}
