{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_017unizhxgjZjVmMLon1BLqL","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/**\n     2→ * Devnet lifecycle E2E test for Lord of the RNGs:\n     3→ * UI create → UI join → countdown → backend settle → verify.\n     4→ */\n     5→import { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\n     6→import type { Page } from \"@playwright/test\";\n     7→import bs58 from \"bs58\";\n     8→import { LordofrngsIDL } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\n     9→import * as po from \"../local/helpers/lord-page-objects\";\n    10→import { PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B } from \"./helpers/wallets\";\n    11→import {\n    12→  validateDevnetEnv,\n    13→  verifyFairnessBackend,\n    14→  type DevnetConfig,\n    15→} from \"./helpers/env\";\n    16→import { withRetry } from \"./helpers/retry\";\n    17→import { ensureLordCleanState } from \"./helpers/lord-on-chain-cleanup\";\n    18→import {\n    19→  getLordProgram,\n    20→  getLordConfigPda,\n    21→  fetchLordRound,\n    22→  assertLordRoundClosed,\n    23→  assertLordTreasuryFee,\n    24→  snapshotBalance,\n    25→  LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n    26→  type JackpotRoundAccount,\n    27→} from \"../local/helpers/on-chain\";\n    28→import { Connection, LAMPORTS_PER_SOL, type PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n    29→\n    30→// ── Devnet wallet funding ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n    31→\n    32→const MIN_BALANCE_SOL = 0.1;\n    33→\n    34→async function ensureFunded(\n    35→  connection: Connection,\n    36→  pubkey: PublicKey,\n    37→  label: string,\n    38→): Promise<void> {\n    39→  const balance = await connection.getBalance(pubkey);\n    40→  if (balance >= MIN_BALANCE_SOL * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL) {\n    41→    console.log(\n    42→      `  ${label}: ${(balance / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL).toFixed(4)} SOL ✓`,\n    43→    );\n    44→    return;\n    45→  }\n    46→  throw new Error(\n    47→    `${label} has ${(balance / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL).toFixed(6)} SOL; ` +\n    48→      `requires at least ${MIN_BALANCE_SOL.toFixed(3)} SOL. ` +\n    49→      `Fund ${pubkey.toBase58()} and rerun.`,\n    50→  );\n    51→}\n    52→\n    53→// ── On-chain constants ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n    54→\n    55→const SETTLEMENT_TIMEOUT_MS = 180_000;\n    56→\n    57→interface BackendLordRoundResponse {\n    58→  pda: string;\n    59→  phase: \"created\" | \"locked\" | \"settling\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\";\n    60→  commitment: string;\n    61→  matchId: string;\n    62→  secret?: string;\n    63→  resultHash?: string | null;\n    64→  winner?: string | null;\n    65→  settleTx?: string | null;\n    66→  entropy?: string | null;\n    67→  winningOffset?: string | null;\n    68→  winningEntryIndex?: number | null;\n    69→  payoutAmount?: number | null;\n    70→  feeAmount?: number | null;\n    71→  rentRefund?: number | null;\n    72→  totalAmountLamports?: number | null;\n    73→}\n    74→\n    75→/** Devnet console noise patterns to ignore. */\n    76→const DEVNET_NOISE = [\n    77→  \"favicon.ico\",\n    78→  \"downloadable font\",\n    79→  \"third-party cookie\",\n    80→  \"429\",\n    81→  \"Too Many Requests\",\n    82→  \"WebSocket\",\n    83→  \"ECONNRESET\",\n    84→  \"socket hang up\",\n    85→  \"FetchError\",\n    86→  \"NetworkError\",\n    87→  \"net::ERR_\",\n    88→  \"ERR_BLOCKED_BY\",\n    89→  \"Failed to load resource\",\n    90→  \"NS_ERROR\",\n    91→  // Expected race: browser auto-claim fires after programmatic claim already closed the round\n    92→  \"AccountNotInitialized\",\n    93→  \"simulation failed BEFORE wallet send\",\n    94→  \"Transaction will fail\",\n    95→];\n    96→\n    97→function filterNoise(errors: string[]): string[] {\n    98→  return errors.filter(\n    99→    (e) => !DEVNET_NOISE.some((p) => e.includes(p)),\n   100→  );\n   101→}\n   102→\n   103→/** Capture [settlement-event] console lines from a page. */\n   104→function captureSettlementEvents(page: Page): string[] {\n   105→  const lines: string[] = [];\n   106→  page.on(\"console\", (msg) => {\n   107→    if (\n   108→      msg.text().includes(\"[settlement-event]\") ||\n   109→      msg.text().includes(\"[lord-of-rngs] settlement-event\")\n   110→    ) {\n   111→      lines.push(msg.text());\n   112→    }\n   113→  });\n   114→  return lines;\n   115→}\n   116→\n   117→async function fetchBackendRound(\n   118→  config: DevnetConfig,\n   119→  roundPda: string,\n   120→): Promise<BackendLordRoundResponse | null> {\n   121→  const response = await fetch(\n   122→    `${config.fairnessBackendUrl}/fairness/rounds/${roundPda}`,\n   123→  );\n   124→  if (response.status === 404) {\n   125→    return null;\n   126→  }\n   127→  if (!response.ok) {\n   128→    throw new Error(\n   129→      `Backend round lookup failed (${response.status} ${response.statusText})`,\n   130→    );\n   131→  }\n   132→  return (await response.json()) as BackendLordRoundResponse;\n   133→}\n   134→\n   135→async function waitForSettledRound(\n   136→  config: DevnetConfig,\n   137→  roundPda: string,\n   138→): Promise<BackendLordRoundResponse> {\n   139→  const start = Date.now();\n   140→\n   141→  while (Date.now() - start < SETTLEMENT_TIMEOUT_MS) {\n   142→    const round = await fetchBackendRound(config, roundPda);\n   143→    if (round?.phase === \"settled\" && round.secret && round.settleTx) {\n   144→      return round;\n   145→    }\n   146→    await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 2_000));\n   147→  }\n   148→\n   149→  throw new Error(`Timed out waiting for backend to settle round ${roundPda}`);\n   150→}\n   151→\n   152→async function findLatestPlayerRound(\n   153→  connection: Connection,\n   154→  player: PublicKey,\n   155→): Promise<{ roundPda: PublicKey; round: JackpotRoundAccount }> {\n   156→  const program = getLordProgram(connection);\n   157→  const discriminator = LordofrngsIDL.accounts.find(\n   158→    (entry) => entry.name === \"JackpotRound\",\n   159→  )?.discriminator;\n   160→  if (!discriminator) {\n   161→    throw new Error(\"JackpotRound discriminator not found in Lord IDL\");\n   162→  }\n   163→\n   164→  const accounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID, {\n   165→    filters: [\n   166→      {\n   167→        memcmp: {\n   168→          offset: 0,\n   169→          bytes: bs58.encode(Uint8Array.from(discriminator)),\n   170→        },\n   171→      },\n   172→    ],\n   173→  });\n   174→\n   175→  const rounds = accounts\n   176→    .map((account) => {\n   177→      try {\n   178→        const round = program.coder.accounts.decode(\n   179→          \"jackpotRound\",\n   180→          account.account.data,\n   181→        ) as JackpotRoundAccount;\n   182→        return { roundPda: account.pubkey, round };\n   183→      } catch {\n   184→        return null;\n   185→      }\n   186→    })\n   187→    .filter(\n   188→      (\n   189→        entry,\n   190→      ): entry is { roundPda: PublicKey; round: JackpotRoundAccount } =>\n   191→        entry !== null,\n   192→    )\n   193→    .filter(({ round }) =>\n   194→      round.entries.some((entry) => entry.player.equals(player)),\n   195→    )\n   196→    .sort((a, b) => b.round.createdAt.toNumber() - a.round.createdAt.toNumber());\n   197→\n   198→  const latest = rounds[0];\n   199→  if (!latest) {\n   200→    throw new Error(`No Lord round found for ${player.toBase58()}`);\n   201→  }\n   202→\n   203→  return latest;\n   204→}\n   205→\n   206→// ── Suite setup ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n   207→\n   208→test.beforeAll(async () => {\n   209→  const config = validateDevnetEnv();\n   210→  if (!config.lordofrngsProgramId) {\n   211→    console.log(\"VITE_LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID not set — skipping Lord lifecycle\");\n   212→    return;\n   213→  }\n   214→  await verifyFairnessBackend(config);\n   215→  console.log(\"Lord devnet lifecycle: checking wallet funding...\");\n   216→  const connection = new Connection(config.rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n   217→  await ensureFunded(connection, PLAYER_A.publicKey, \"Player A\");\n   218→  await ensureFunded(connection, PLAYER_B.publicKey, \"Player B\");\n   219→});\n   220→\n   221→// ── Full lifecycle test ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n   222→\n   223→test(\"lord lifecycle: UI create → UI join → countdown → backend settle → verify\", async ({\n   224→  playerAPage,\n   225→  playerBPage,\n   226→  connection,\n   227→  devnetConfig,\n   228→}) => {\n   229→  if (!devnetConfig.lordofrngsProgramId) {\n   230→    test.skip(true, \"VITE_LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID not configured\");\n   231→    return;\n   232→  }\n   233→\n   234→  test.setTimeout(300_000);\n   235→\n   236→  // ── Pre-flight: clean stale rounds ──────────────────────────────────\n   237→  const cleanupResults = await Promise.allSettled([\n   238→    ensureLordCleanState(connection, PLAYER_A, \"Player A\"),\n   239→    ensureLordCleanState(connection, PLAYER_B, \"Player B\"),\n   240→  ]);\n   241→  for (const result of cleanupResults) {\n   242→    if (result.status === \"rejected\") {\n   243→      const err = result.reason;\n   244→      if (\n   245→        err instanceof Error &&\n   246→        err.message.includes(\"Settlement in-flight\")\n   247→      ) {\n   248→        test.skip(true, err.message);\n   249→      }\n   250→      throw err;\n   251→    }\n   252→  }\n   253→\n   254→  const consoleA = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerAPage);\n   255→  const consoleB = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerBPage);\n   256→\n   257→  // Capture settlement event WebSocket logs from both players\n   258→  const settlementEventsA = captureSettlementEvents(playerAPage);\n   259→  const settlementEventsB = captureSettlementEvents(playerBPage);\n   260→\n   261→  console.log(\"[phase-1] Player A navigating to Lord of RNGs...\");\n   262→  await po.navigateToLord(playerAPage);\n   263→\n   264→  const startBtn = playerAPage.locator(po.sel.actionButton, {\n   265→    hasText: /Start Round/i,\n   266→  });\n   267→  await expect(startBtn).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });\n   268→  console.log(\"[phase-1] 'Start Round' button visible ✓\");\n   269→\n   270→  await startBtn.click();\n   271→  console.log(\"[phase-1] Clicked 'Start Round', waiting for round to appear...\");\n   272→\n   273→  await playerAPage.waitForSelector(\n   274→    `${po.sel.activeRound}, ${po.sel.wheelLegendItem}`,\n   275→    { state: \"visible\", timeout: 60_000 },\n   276→  );\n   277→  console.log(\"[phase-1] Player A round created via UI ✓\");\n   278→\n   279→  const { roundPda, round: createdOnChainRound } = await withRetry(\n   280→    () =>\n   281→      findLatestPlayerRound(\n   282→        connection,\n   283→        PLAYER_A.publicKey,\n   284→      ),\n   285→    { label: \"findLatestPlayerRound\", retries: 10, delayMs: 1_000 },\n   286→  );\n   287→  let round = createdOnChainRound;\n   288→  const matchIdHex = Array.from(round.matchId as number[]).map((b: number) => b.toString(16).padStart(2, \"0\")).join(\"\");\n   289→  console.log(`[on-chain] Round PDA: ${roundPda.toBase58().slice(0, 12)}…, matchId=${matchIdHex}`);\n   290→  expect(round.entries.length).toBe(1);\n   291→\n   292→  const createdRound = await withRetry(\n   293→    async () => {\n   294→      const backendRound = await fetchBackendRound(devnetConfig, roundPda.toBase58());\n   295→      expect(backendRound).not.toBeNull();\n   296→      expect(backendRound?.phase).toBe(\"created\");\n   297→      expect(backendRound?.secret).toBeUndefined();\n   298→      return backendRound!;\n   299→    },\n   300→    { label: \"backend lord round created\", retries: 10, delayMs: 1_000 },\n   301→  );\n   302→  console.log(\n   303→    `[backend] Round created with commitment ${createdRound.commitment.slice(0, 12)}...`,\n   304→  );\n   305→\n   306→  console.log(\"[phase-2] Player B navigating...\");\n   307→  await po.navigateToLord(playerBPage);\n   308→  await expect(playerBPage.locator(po.sel.tierCard).first()).toBeVisible({\n   309→    timeout: 15_000,\n   310→  });\n   311→  await po.selectTier(playerBPage, 0);\n   312→\n   313→  // \"Join Round\" must be visible — proves Player B sees the existing round\n   314→  const joinBtn = playerBPage.locator(po.sel.actionButton, {\n   315→    hasText: /Join Round/i,\n   316→  });\n   317→  await expect(joinBtn).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });\n   318→  console.log(\"[phase-2] 'Join Round' button visible ✓\");\n   319→\n   320→  await joinBtn.click();\n   321→  console.log(\"[phase-2] Clicked 'Join Round', waiting for UI update...\");\n   322→\n   323→  await playerBPage.waitForSelector(\n   324→    `${po.sel.activeRound}, ${po.sel.wheelLegendItem}`,\n   325→    { state: \"visible\", timeout: 60_000 },\n   326→  );\n   327→  console.log(\"[phase-2] Player B joined via UI ✓\");\n   328→\n   329→  round = await withRetry(\n   330→    async () => {\n   331→      const r = await fetchLordRound(connection, roundPda);\n   332→      if (!r) throw new Error(\"Round PDA not found\");\n   333→      if (r.entries.length < 2) throw new Error(`Only ${r.entries.length} entry(s)`);\n   334→      return r;\n   335→    },\n   336→    { label: \"verifyTwoEntries\", retries: 5, delayMs: 3_000 },\n   337→  );\n   338→  expect(round.entries.length).toBe(2);\n   339→  const phase = Object.keys(round.phase)[0];\n   340→  console.log(`[on-chain] phase=\"${phase}\", entries=${round.entries.length} ✓`);\n   341→  expect(phase).toBe(\"active\");\n   342→\n   343→  const lordProgram = getLordProgram(connection);\n   344→  const [lordConfigPda] = getLordConfigPda();\n   345→  const lordConfig = await lordProgram.account.lordConfig.fetch(lordConfigPda);\n   346→  const treasury = (lordConfig as unknown as { treasury: PublicKey }).treasury;\n   347→  const treasuryBefore = await snapshotBalance(connection, treasury);\n   348→\n   349→  const settledRound = await waitForSettledRound(\n   350→    devnetConfig,\n   351→    roundPda.toBase58(),\n   352→  );\n   353→  console.log(`[backend] Round settled via ${settledRound.settleTx}`);\n   354→\n   355→  await Promise.all([\n   356→    po.waitForSettlementUi(playerAPage, 120_000),\n   357→    po.waitForSettlementUi(playerBPage, 120_000),\n   358→  ]);\n   359→  expect([\n   360→    PLAYER_A.publicKey.toBase58(),\n   361→    PLAYER_B.publicKey.toBase58(),\n   362→  ]).toContain(settledRound.winner);\n   363→\n   364→  expect(settledRound.secret).toMatch(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/i);\n   365→  expect(settledRound.commitment).toMatch(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/i);\n   366→  expect(settledRound.resultHash ?? \"\").toMatch(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/i);\n   367→  expect(settledRound.entropy ?? \"\").toMatch(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/i);\n   368→  expect(settledRound.winner).toBeTruthy();\n   369→  expect(settledRound.settleTx).toBeTruthy();\n   370→\n   371→  await withRetry(\n   372→    () => assertLordRoundClosed(connection, roundPda),\n   373→    { label: \"assertRoundClosed\" },\n   374→  );\n   375→  console.log(\"[phase-3] Round PDA closed after backend settlement ✓\");\n   376→\n   377→  await withRetry(\n   378→    () =>\n   379→      assertLordTreasuryFee(\n   380→        connection,\n   381→        treasury,\n   382→        treasuryBefore,\n   383→        settledRound.totalAmountLamports ?? round.totalAmountLamports.toNumber(),\n   384→      ),\n   385→    { label: \"assertTreasuryFee\" },\n   386→  );\n   387→  console.log(\"[phase-3] Treasury fee verified ✓\");\n   388→\n   389→  // ── Verify settlement event subscription fired ─────────────────────\n   390→  const allSettlementEvents = [...settlementEventsA, ...settlementEventsB];\n   391→  console.log(\n   392→    `[settlement-event] captured ${allSettlementEvents.length} event log(s):`,\n   393→  );\n   394→  allSettlementEvents.forEach((line) => console.log(`  ${line}`));\n   395→\n   396→  const subscribed = allSettlementEvents.some((l) => l.includes(\"subscribed\"));\n   397→  const matched = allSettlementEvents.some(\n   398→    (l) => l.includes(\"matched\") || l.includes(\"settlement-event received\"),\n   399→  );\n   400→  expect(subscribed).toBe(true);\n   401→  if (!matched) {\n   402→    console.warn(\n   403→      \"[settlement-event] WARNING: event subscription was active but \" +\n   404→        \"roundSettled event was not detected — polling won the race.\",\n   405→    );\n   406→  } else {\n   407→    console.log(\"[settlement-event] roundSettled event detected via WebSocket ✓\");\n   408→  }\n   409→\n   410→  const errA = filterNoise(consoleA.errors);\n   411→  const errB = filterNoise(consoleB.errors);\n   412→  expect(errA).toEqual([]);\n   413→  expect(errB).toEqual([]);\n   414→});\n   415→"}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1de1cbce-bcf6-4659-9a0e-c65f55d25303","uuid":"a6c41db9-587f-4ea6-a803-1583540bad64","tool_use_result":{"type":"text","file":{"filePath":"/workspaces/rng-utopia/sources/rng-utopia/apps/platform/e2e/devnet/lord-lifecycle.spec.ts","content":"/**\n * Devnet lifecycle E2E test for Lord of the RNGs:\n * UI create → UI join → countdown → backend settle → verify.\n */\nimport { test, expect } from \"./fixtures\";\nimport type { Page } from \"@playwright/test\";\nimport bs58 from \"bs58\";\nimport { LordofrngsIDL } from \"@rng-utopia/anchor-client\";\nimport * as po from \"../local/helpers/lord-page-objects\";\nimport { PLAYER_A, PLAYER_B } from \"./helpers/wallets\";\nimport {\n  validateDevnetEnv,\n  verifyFairnessBackend,\n  type DevnetConfig,\n} from \"./helpers/env\";\nimport { withRetry } from \"./helpers/retry\";\nimport { ensureLordCleanState } from \"./helpers/lord-on-chain-cleanup\";\nimport {\n  getLordProgram,\n  getLordConfigPda,\n  fetchLordRound,\n  assertLordRoundClosed,\n  assertLordTreasuryFee,\n  snapshotBalance,\n  LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID,\n  type JackpotRoundAccount,\n} from \"../local/helpers/on-chain\";\nimport { Connection, LAMPORTS_PER_SOL, type PublicKey } from \"@solana/web3.js\";\n\n// ── Devnet wallet funding ─────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst MIN_BALANCE_SOL = 0.1;\n\nasync function ensureFunded(\n  connection: Connection,\n  pubkey: PublicKey,\n  label: string,\n): Promise<void> {\n  const balance = await connection.getBalance(pubkey);\n  if (balance >= MIN_BALANCE_SOL * LAMPORTS_PER_SOL) {\n    console.log(\n      `  ${label}: ${(balance / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL).toFixed(4)} SOL ✓`,\n    );\n    return;\n  }\n  throw new Error(\n    `${label} has ${(balance / LAMPORTS_PER_SOL).toFixed(6)} SOL; ` +\n      `requires at least ${MIN_BALANCE_SOL.toFixed(3)} SOL. ` +\n      `Fund ${pubkey.toBase58()} and rerun.`,\n  );\n}\n\n// ── On-chain constants ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n\nconst SETTLEMENT_TIMEOUT_MS = 180_000;\n\ninterface BackendLordRoundResponse {\n  pda: string;\n  phase: \"created\" | \"locked\" | \"settling\" | \"settled\" | \"expired\";\n  commitment: string;\n  matchId: string;\n  secret?: string;\n  resultHash?: string | null;\n  winner?: string | null;\n  settleTx?: string | null;\n  entropy?: string | null;\n  winningOffset?: string | null;\n  winningEntryIndex?: number | null;\n  payoutAmount?: number | null;\n  feeAmount?: number | null;\n  rentRefund?: number | null;\n  totalAmountLamports?: number | null;\n}\n\n/** Devnet console noise patterns to ignore. */\nconst DEVNET_NOISE = [\n  \"favicon.ico\",\n  \"downloadable font\",\n  \"third-party cookie\",\n  \"429\",\n  \"Too Many Requests\",\n  \"WebSocket\",\n  \"ECONNRESET\",\n  \"socket hang up\",\n  \"FetchError\",\n  \"NetworkError\",\n  \"net::ERR_\",\n  \"ERR_BLOCKED_BY\",\n  \"Failed to load resource\",\n  \"NS_ERROR\",\n  // Expected race: browser auto-claim fires after programmatic claim already closed the round\n  \"AccountNotInitialized\",\n  \"simulation failed BEFORE wallet send\",\n  \"Transaction will fail\",\n];\n\nfunction filterNoise(errors: string[]): string[] {\n  return errors.filter(\n    (e) => !DEVNET_NOISE.some((p) => e.includes(p)),\n  );\n}\n\n/** Capture [settlement-event] console lines from a page. */\nfunction captureSettlementEvents(page: Page): string[] {\n  const lines: string[] = [];\n  page.on(\"console\", (msg) => {\n    if (\n      msg.text().includes(\"[settlement-event]\") ||\n      msg.text().includes(\"[lord-of-rngs] settlement-event\")\n    ) {\n      lines.push(msg.text());\n    }\n  });\n  return lines;\n}\n\nasync function fetchBackendRound(\n  config: DevnetConfig,\n  roundPda: string,\n): Promise<BackendLordRoundResponse | null> {\n  const response = await fetch(\n    `${config.fairnessBackendUrl}/fairness/rounds/${roundPda}`,\n  );\n  if (response.status === 404) {\n    return null;\n  }\n  if (!response.ok) {\n    throw new Error(\n      `Backend round lookup failed (${response.status} ${response.statusText})`,\n    );\n  }\n  return (await response.json()) as BackendLordRoundResponse;\n}\n\nasync function waitForSettledRound(\n  config: DevnetConfig,\n  roundPda: string,\n): Promise<BackendLordRoundResponse> {\n  const start = Date.now();\n\n  while (Date.now() - start < SETTLEMENT_TIMEOUT_MS) {\n    const round = await fetchBackendRound(config, roundPda);\n    if (round?.phase === \"settled\" && round.secret && round.settleTx) {\n      return round;\n    }\n    await new Promise((resolve) => setTimeout(resolve, 2_000));\n  }\n\n  throw new Error(`Timed out waiting for backend to settle round ${roundPda}`);\n}\n\nasync function findLatestPlayerRound(\n  connection: Connection,\n  player: PublicKey,\n): Promise<{ roundPda: PublicKey; round: JackpotRoundAccount }> {\n  const program = getLordProgram(connection);\n  const discriminator = LordofrngsIDL.accounts.find(\n    (entry) => entry.name === \"JackpotRound\",\n  )?.discriminator;\n  if (!discriminator) {\n    throw new Error(\"JackpotRound discriminator not found in Lord IDL\");\n  }\n\n  const accounts = await connection.getProgramAccounts(LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID, {\n    filters: [\n      {\n        memcmp: {\n          offset: 0,\n          bytes: bs58.encode(Uint8Array.from(discriminator)),\n        },\n      },\n    ],\n  });\n\n  const rounds = accounts\n    .map((account) => {\n      try {\n        const round = program.coder.accounts.decode(\n          \"jackpotRound\",\n          account.account.data,\n        ) as JackpotRoundAccount;\n        return { roundPda: account.pubkey, round };\n      } catch {\n        return null;\n      }\n    })\n    .filter(\n      (\n        entry,\n      ): entry is { roundPda: PublicKey; round: JackpotRoundAccount } =>\n        entry !== null,\n    )\n    .filter(({ round }) =>\n      round.entries.some((entry) => entry.player.equals(player)),\n    )\n    .sort((a, b) => b.round.createdAt.toNumber() - a.round.createdAt.toNumber());\n\n  const latest = rounds[0];\n  if (!latest) {\n    throw new Error(`No Lord round found for ${player.toBase58()}`);\n  }\n\n  return latest;\n}\n\n// ── Suite setup ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ntest.beforeAll(async () => {\n  const config = validateDevnetEnv();\n  if (!config.lordofrngsProgramId) {\n    console.log(\"VITE_LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID not set — skipping Lord lifecycle\");\n    return;\n  }\n  await verifyFairnessBackend(config);\n  console.log(\"Lord devnet lifecycle: checking wallet funding...\");\n  const connection = new Connection(config.rpcUrl, \"confirmed\");\n  await ensureFunded(connection, PLAYER_A.publicKey, \"Player A\");\n  await ensureFunded(connection, PLAYER_B.publicKey, \"Player B\");\n});\n\n// ── Full lifecycle test ───────────────────────────────────────────────\n\ntest(\"lord lifecycle: UI create → UI join → countdown → backend settle → verify\", async ({\n  playerAPage,\n  playerBPage,\n  connection,\n  devnetConfig,\n}) => {\n  if (!devnetConfig.lordofrngsProgramId) {\n    test.skip(true, \"VITE_LORDOFRNGS_PROGRAM_ID not configured\");\n    return;\n  }\n\n  test.setTimeout(300_000);\n\n  // ── Pre-flight: clean stale rounds ──────────────────────────────────\n  const cleanupResults = await Promise.allSettled([\n    ensureLordCleanState(connection, PLAYER_A, \"Player A\"),\n    ensureLordCleanState(connection, PLAYER_B, \"Player B\"),\n  ]);\n  for (const result of cleanupResults) {\n    if (result.status === \"rejected\") {\n      const err = result.reason;\n      if (\n        err instanceof Error &&\n        err.message.includes(\"Settlement in-flight\")\n      ) {\n        test.skip(true, err.message);\n      }\n      throw err;\n    }\n  }\n\n  const consoleA = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerAPage);\n  const consoleB = po.trackConsoleErrors(playerBPage);\n\n  // Capture settlement event WebSocket logs from both players\n  const settlementEventsA = captureSettlementEvents(playerAPage);\n  const settlementEventsB = captureSettlementEvents(playerBPage);\n\n  console.log(\"[phase-1] Player A navigating to Lord of RNGs...\");\n  await po.navigateToLord(playerAPage);\n\n  const startBtn = playerAPage.locator(po.sel.actionButton, {\n    hasText: /Start Round/i,\n  });\n  await expect(startBtn).toBeVisible({ timeout: 10_000 });\n  console.log(\"[phase-1] 'Start Round' button visible ✓\");\n\n  await startBtn.click();\n  console.log(\"[phase-1] Clicked 'Start Round', waiting for round to appear...\");\n\n  await playerAPage.waitForSelector(\n    `${po.sel.activeRound}, ${po.sel.wheelLegendItem}`,\n    { state: \"visible\", timeout: 60_000 },\n  );\n  console.log(\"[phase-1] Player A round created via UI ✓\");\n\n  const { roundPda, round: createdOnChainRound } = await withRetry(\n    () =>\n      findLatestPlayerRound(\n        connection,\n        PLAYER_A.publicKey,\n      ),\n    { label: \"findLatestPlayerRound\", retries: 10, delayMs: 1_000 },\n  );\n  let round = createdOnChainRound;\n  const matchIdHex = Array.from(round.matchId as number[]).map((b: number) => b.toString(16).padStart(2, \"0\")).join(\"\");\n  console.log(`[on-chain] Round PDA: ${roundPda.toBase58().slice(0, 12)}…, matchId=${matchIdHex}`);\n  expect(round.entries.length).toBe(1);\n\n  const createdRound = await withRetry(\n    async () => {\n      const backendRound = await fetchBackendRound(devnetConfig, roundPda.toBase58());\n      expect(backendRound).not.toBeNull();\n      expect(backendRound?.phase).toBe(\"created\");\n      expect(backendRound?.secret).toBeUndefined();\n      return backendRound!;\n    },\n    { label: \"backend lord round created\", retries: 10, delayMs: 1_000 },\n  );\n  console.log(\n    `[backend] Round created with commitment ${createdRound.commitment.slice(0, 12)}...`,\n  );\n\n  console.log(\"[phase-2] Player B navigating...\");\n  await po.navigateToLord(playerBPage);\n  await expect(playerBPage.locator(po.sel.tierCard).first()).toBeVisible({\n    timeout: 15_000,\n  });\n  await po.selectTier(playerBPage, 0);\n\n  // \"Join Round\" must be visible — proves Player B sees the existing round\n  const joinBtn = playerBPage.locator(po.sel.actionButton, {\n    hasText: /Join Round/i,\n  });\n  await expect(joinBtn).toBeVisible({ timeout: 15_000 });\n  console.log(\"[phase-2] 'Join Round' button visible ✓\");\n\n  await joinBtn.click();\n  console.log(\"[phase-2] Clicked 'Join Round', waiting for UI update...\");\n\n  await playerBPage.waitForSelector(\n    `${po.sel.activeRound}, ${po.sel.wheelLegendItem}`,\n    { state: \"visible\", timeout: 60_000 },\n  );\n  console.log(\"[phase-2] Player B joined via UI ✓\");\n\n  round = await withRetry(\n    async () => {\n      const r = await fetchLordRound(connection, roundPda);\n      if (!r) throw new Error(\"Round PDA not found\");\n      if (r.entries.length < 2) throw new Error(`Only ${r.entries.length} entry(s)`);\n      return r;\n    },\n    { label: \"verifyTwoEntries\", retries: 5, delayMs: 3_000 },\n  );\n  expect(round.entries.length).toBe(2);\n  const phase = Object.keys(round.phase)[0];\n  console.log(`[on-chain] phase=\"${phase}\", entries=${round.entries.length} ✓`);\n  expect(phase).toBe(\"active\");\n\n  const lordProgram = getLordProgram(connection);\n  const [lordConfigPda] = getLordConfigPda();\n  const lordConfig = await lordProgram.account.lordConfig.fetch(lordConfigPda);\n  const treasury = (lordConfig as unknown as { treasury: PublicKey }).treasury;\n  const treasuryBefore = await snapshotBalance(connection, treasury);\n\n  const settledRound = await waitForSettledRound(\n    devnetConfig,\n    roundPda.toBase58(),\n  );\n  console.log(`[backend] Round settled via ${settledRound.settleTx}`);\n\n  await Promise.all([\n    po.waitForSettlementUi(playerAPage, 120_000),\n    po.waitForSettlementUi(playerBPage, 120_000),\n  ]);\n  expect([\n    PLAYER_A.publicKey.toBase58(),\n    PLAYER_B.publicKey.toBase58(),\n  ]).toContain(settledRound.winner);\n\n  expect(settledRound.secret).toMatch(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/i);\n  expect(settledRound.commitment).toMatch(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/i);\n  expect(settledRound.resultHash ?? \"\").toMatch(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/i);\n  expect(settledRound.entropy ?? \"\").toMatch(/^[0-9a-f]{64}$/i);\n  expect(settledRound.winner).toBeTruthy();\n  expect(settledRound.settleTx).toBeTruthy();\n\n  await withRetry(\n    () => assertLordRoundClosed(connection, roundPda),\n    { label: \"assertRoundClosed\" },\n  );\n  console.log(\"[phase-3] Round PDA closed after backend settlement ✓\");\n\n  await withRetry(\n    () =>\n      assertLordTreasuryFee(\n        connection,\n        treasury,\n        treasuryBefore,\n        settledRound.totalAmountLamports ?? round.totalAmountLamports.toNumber(),\n      ),\n    { label: \"assertTreasuryFee\" },\n  );\n  console.log(\"[phase-3] Treasury fee verified ✓\");\n\n  // ── Verify settlement event subscription fired ─────────────────────\n  const allSettlementEvents = [...settlementEventsA, ...settlementEventsB];\n  console.log(\n    `[settlement-event] captured ${allSettlementEvents.length} event log(s):`,\n  );\n  allSettlementEvents.forEach((line) => console.log(`  ${line}`));\n\n  const subscribed = allSettlementEvents.some((l) => l.includes(\"subscribed\"));\n  const matched = allSettlementEvents.some(\n    (l) => l.includes(\"matched\") || l.includes(\"settlement-event received\"),\n  );\n  expect(subscribed).toBe(true);\n  if (!matched) {\n    console.warn(\n      \"[settlement-event] WARNING: event subscription was active but \" +\n        \"roundSettled event was not detected — polling won the race.\",\n    );\n  } else {\n    console.log(\"[settlement-event] roundSettled event detected via WebSocket ✓\");\n  }\n\n  const errA = filterNoise(consoleA.errors);\n  const errB = filterNoise(consoleB.errors);\n  expect(errA).toEqual([]);\n  expect(errB).toEqual([]);\n});\n","numLines":415,"startLine":1,"totalLines":415}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-6","id":"msg_018U6Wo6Qkfi7M9Tub43wZX4","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a thorough understanding of the devnet E2E patterns. Let me think about what the Close Call devnet E2E test should look like.\n\nKey differences from Coinflip/Lord:\n1. Rounds are backend-managed (clock worker creates them), not player-initiated\n2. Settlement is automatic (no player action needed) via Pyth oracle\n3. We can't control when rounds open/close\n4. Pyth devnet prices are stale (~5 min updates), so the clock worker may fail to create rounds\n\nGiven these constraints, I should create:\n\n1. **Updated `helpers/env.ts`**: Add `closecallProgramId` to `DevnetConfig`, validate `VITE_CLOSECALL_PROGRAM_ID`\n\n\n2. **`closecall-lifecycle.spec.ts`**: A devnet E2E test that validates the environment and Pyth price account, then polls for an open round and executes the betting flow if one exists—with both players placing opposing bets and verifying settlement outcomes, or confirming the API gracefully handles unavailable rounds due to Pyth staleness.\n\nGiven the clock worker's frequent failures from stale Pyth prices on devnet, I'm splitting this into two tiers: a foundational tier that always runs to validate the program deployment, Pyth account readability, and API responsiveness, and a conditional tier that only attempts the full betting lifecycle if an active round with an open window is available. Now I need to design the actual test structure.\n\nI'm checking the backend API endpoints for closecall — they're under the `/closecall` prefix with routes for fetching the current round and historical data. I'll update the environment configuration to include the closecall program ID, extend the deployment verification to check that program, and create the lifecycle test file. I also need to confirm the Pyth BTC/USD price account address from devnet, which should be the standard one.\n\nNow I'm looking at what page objects or selectors exist for the close-call page, and I need to review the Playwright devnet configuration to understand how test matching patterns work.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":6535,"cache_read_input_tokens":64919,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":6535},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1de1cbce-bcf6-4659-9a0e-c65f55d25303","uuid":"0cf0d126-2482-4018-b4e5-aea687757b95"}
